title: giant ginger cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and spices.
Set aside. In large bowl, beat shortening until softened.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and molasses; beat well.
Add half of flour; beat until combined.
Stir in remaining flour with a wooden spoon.
Using a 1/4-cup ice cream scoop, shape dough into 2-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown and puffed.
Let stand 2 minutes before transferring to a wire rack.
Cool.
Makes about 25 cookies.

title: grits supreme for breakfast
directions: Prepare grits as usual.
In another pan, combine margarine, soup, tuna fish and mushrooms.
Allow these ingredients to simmer for just a few minutes, until they are well mixed and hot.
Serve over individual servings of grits.
Delightful.

title: *florentine salad
directions: Mix together in small bowl the oil, vinegar, garlic, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add tomatoes and let marinate for 1 hour or longer.
Wash spinach and tear into pieces.
Separate endive into leaves.
Refrigerate both.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 2 tablespoons of milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: coconut shortbread pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat mixture in 9-inch pie dish.
Chill 30 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: vermont chocolate fudge
directions: Heat water to 225° for 4 minutes; gradually add morsels 1/2 cup at a time, letting them melt after each addition.
Add syrup and marshmallows; stir until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Serve fondue with fruit, cake or whatever sounds delicious.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour slowly with baking soda. Press onto cookie pan and smooth out with glass cup.
Prick all over.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Cut into squares while hot.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti up into thirds in boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Rinse with cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Serves at least 20.

title: sparkling fruit cocktail
directions: In a large bowl, combine bananas, grapes, orange segments and orange juice; mix well and chill for several hours.
Spoon into sherbet glasses, adding ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cobbler cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: english muffins in a loaf(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Combine 3 cups flour (may use 1 1/2 whole wheat and 1 1/2 white flour), yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat milk and water to 120°. Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in enough flour to make a very stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans that are greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise in warm place 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: vegetables and pasta
directions: 1. Boil pasta until almost done. Add broccoli for one minute. Add remaining vegetables and immediately drain.
2. Mix pasta, vegetables, salad dressing, and seasonings
in a large dish and serve while warm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Peel and slice zucchini.
Cut into large diced pieces.
Cook in salted water just until tender.
Remove and drain; set aside. Using 4 tablespoons butter, saute onions and carrots until onions are translucent.
Add 1 1/2 cups bread.
Put in ovensafe dish. Add sour cream and soup; mix.
Add drained zucchini and mix carefully.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan and toss with remaining bread and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo until limp, but not brown. Combine rice, broccoli, onions, celery, cream of chicken soup, mushrooms and Cheez Whiz; mix well and put into a large casserole. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
The ingredients make a heap.
If desired, can be halved or made into smaller casseroles and frozen.
Also good for church gathering.

title: one
directions: Place rice in bottom of buttered casserole.
Mix soup, soup mix and water; pour 2/3 over rice.
Lay chicken over rice.
Pour remaining soup mixture over all.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Cook roast and all the ingredients in crock-pot until tender. Shred meat and allow to simmer in broth for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove bay leaves before serving.	Serve on toasted rolls.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring. Add eggs; beat well until smooth.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into mixture and work well.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 10 minutes or until brown at 400°.

title: marinade for roast
directions: Marinate for 3 to 24 hours.
Enough for a 3 pound roast.
Turn meat several times so marinade will soak in.
Cook meat in the marinade.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter.
Add flour, soda and nuts.
This can be rolled and chilled or dropped from spoon, the size of a walnut and pressed with a glass dipped in sugar to very flat cookie.

title: special forces steak
directions: Other vegetables or greens can be substituted or added if desired for a full course meal.
Double a 12 x 20-inch of foil. Place meat in foil.
Place vegetables on top of meat.
Seal by wrapping foil around this.
Toss this into camp fire for about 30 minutes or in oven if available at 350°.
Open foil and eat out of it.
Foil can keep the contents hot if out in cold.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Chop onions and cook until tender. Drain tuna; place noodles, onions and tuna in casserole dish.
Mix well.
Stir in mushroom soup and milk.
Melt butter in separate pan.
Crush crackers; mix with butter.
Spread over noodle mixture 10 minutes before removing from oven.
Place in 350° oven until boiling edges.
(Remember crackers for top.)
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creole green beans
directions: Cook bacon and drain; reserve drippings.
Place beans and tomatoes in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper and 3 to 4 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Crumble bacon on top.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa over low heat.
Mix in eggs, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake mincemeat pie
directions: Prepare and bake pie shell; cool.
Combine the mincemeat and 1/3 cup walnuts.
Spoon mixture into pie shell and spread evenly in a mixer bowl; beat cream cheese, eggs, 1/3 cup sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour over mincemeat and spread evenly.
Bake in a 375° oven about 25 minutes or until nearly set.
Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Spread over pie and top with remaining walnuts.
Bake 5 minutes; chill 5 hours before serving.

title: fruit parfaits
directions: Combine orange juice and sugar, mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
In another bowl, combine fruit pieces.
In 2 parfait glasses, alternately layer fruit, marshmallows, and then whipped topping mixture; repeat.
Chill.
May be topped with a maraschino cherry.

title: zucchini in wine
directions: Heat wine to boiling in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in zucchini, garlic and basil.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in onion.
Cook uncovered until zucchini is crisp and tender and liquid is reduced, 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: cinnamon cheesecake squares
directions: Spread 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until smooth.
Spread on crescent rolls, then top with 2nd package of crescent rolls.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut steak into serving size portions and place on cookie sheet.
Pour marinade over pieces, turning meat to cover both sides.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
In morning, remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature for an hour or two before cooking, turning frequently.
Grill until desired doneness.

title: berry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, salt, cornstarch and cinnamon. Stir in berries.
Add water, lemon juice and oleo or butter.
Cook over medium heat just to a boiling point.
Pour berry mixture into pie shell; pour 1 teaspoon milk over top and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake in 400° oven until crust is a golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into ball.
Chill.
Roll in nuts and parsley.

title: bow tie with marinara
directions: Combine pasta and sauce. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: deer steak and gravy
directions: Tenderize meat.
Add salt and pepper and roll in flour. Brown on both sides.
Put water, onion, salt, garlic cloves, garlic salt and bouillon cubes in Dutch oven.
Drop in meat. Simmer for 45 minutes or until gravy is thick and creamy.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix tomato soup with ground beef, uncooked rice, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into balls about 1-1/2 inch in diameter (about 16).

title: lemon dream cake
directions: Bake lemon cake mix according to directions on package for 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes. Stir together lemonade concentrate and powdered sugar. Blend thoroughly. Poke top of warm cake every 1/2-inch with long-tined fork, wiping fork occasionally to reduce sticking. Drizzle lemonade mixture evenly over top of cake. Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled. Spread frosting of your choice over top of cake and sprinkle with sugar for garnish. Cover loosely and refrigerate until serving time. Any remaining cake should be refrigerated.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325° (for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt oleo in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over oleo.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: party cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients; sprinkle wax paper with paprika and roll cheese roll.
Wrap in
foil
and
chill.
Slice as needed. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain, then add ketchup, salt and tomato sauce.
Heat until boiling.

title: chocolate almond pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and candy bars in milk in double boiler. Remove from heat and cool. Whip the cream until stiff and fold into cooled mixture. Add vanilla. Pour into prepared crust and chill. Top with whipped cream.

title: apricot squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in oats and brown sugar.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter or margarine as for pie crust. Divide in half.
Put a little over half in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat gently.
Cover with jam (apricot, raspberry, strawberry, etc.). Cover with remaining crumbs.
Pat gently.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: marshmallow surprise
directions: Separate rolls.
Dip marshmallows in melted margarine, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place 1 in each crescent and wrap, pinching edges together.
Place in muffin tins and pour remaining melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt margarine and add sugar, cocoa and milk. Add corn syrup. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 3 minutes. Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Stir in oatmeal until well blended. Remove from heat and beat mixture until slightly thickened. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients for crust.
Mix next 3 ingredients for filling.
Put pie filling on top.

title: rum cake with chocolate cream cheese icing
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directions, substituting 1/3 cup rum for 1/3 cup water.
Divide batter equally among 3 greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake about 23 minutes at 350°.
Cool layers 30 minutes.
Can drizzle layers with additional rum.

title: corny dogs
directions: Beat together and dip skewered hot dogs in batter before deep frying.
A corn-on-the-cob dish is a good shape for dipping when batter gets low.
Makes 15 to 16 corny dogs.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add all other ingredients and beat well. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts (if desired) on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook hen tender with plenty of broth.
Slip meat off bones. Put Croutettes in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients and soften with broth.
Stir together until there are no lumps.
Add 8 eggs and mix well.
Put in pan and add chicken.
Pour broth over until well soaked.
Bake at 400° until done, but not dry.
Serve with giblet gravy.

title: easy peach nectar cake
directions: Beat ingredients on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a well greased 9 by 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet or into ungreased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Mix margarine and garlic; brush over warm biscuits and serve.

title: strawberry butter spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well until blended and smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Delicious on toast or hot rolls.

title: banana yams
directions: Peel and quarter the yams.
Cook for 20 minutes in boiling salted water; drain.
Cut into 1-inch cubes; add bananas, cut into thick slices.
Add the pineapple chunks and half the juice.
Add the cherries that have been cut in half and the marshmallows.
Stir gently to mix the ingredients.
Put into a buttered baking dish. Pour the melted butter over the top; sprinkle on the brown sugar and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheese shrimp
directions: Cook the 2 soups over low heat in porcelain pan.
Add cheese; stir while cooking.
After cheese melts, add cleaned raw shrimp. Cook over low heat for about 15 minutes, stirring frequently, or until shrimp are done.
Serve over rice.

title: dieter's delight cake
directions: Boil raisins in water until almost dry.
Mix applesauce, oil, eggs, vanilla, pecans and 7 packages of Sweet 'N Low together and set aside.
Mix soda, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and 9 packages of Sweet 'N Low.
Put all together and mix well.
Place in oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Bake until done. Twenty-four servings = 1 fruit and 1 bread.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
In big pan, mix all ingredients until well blended.
Line the bottom of large loaf pan with waxed paper. Cover the sides of the pan too, then put paper on top and press down.
Keep covered and refrigerate several days.

title: stewed chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large pot; add blackberry wine and both bottles of barbecue sauce.
Cook on low heat until chicken falls off bones.
Stir occasionally.
Cook about 2 hours.
Serve extra gravy for other meals.
Pour gravy over chicken and rice.

title: cabbage bundles
directions: Mix hamburger, seasonings, onion, rice and egg as you would a meat loaf.
Set aside.
Wilt cabbage leaves in boiling water. Form logs of meat mixture and roll in leaves.
Place in pan that has a lid.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce and 1 can water over this. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: nina's jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Mix wet ingredients (eggs, sugar, oil, juice or milk and vanilla).
Next, put in flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Mix well to make batter. Grease well a Bundt pan.
Add 1/3 batter and place apple mix on top.
Do alternately, first batter, then apple mixture until all is used.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Check with toothpick to make sure it is done.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes in chunks. Chop onions and peppers fine. Mix together and add vinegar, salt, sugar and black pepper and cook 15 minutes. Do not boil. Jar while hot and seal. This usually makes about 15 pints.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake well.
Store in refrigerator.
Calories per tablespoon are 8.

title: salsa
directions: Chop or blend all vegetables.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour into hot jars.
Freeze when cooled.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: black beans
directions: Before cooking, wash beans and soak 4 to 5 hours.
Water should cover beans by 1 1/2 inches.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 onion and 1 green pepper to beans.
After soaking, bring beans to boil uncovered.
When boiling, add bacon.
Cover and lower to medium heat for 1 hour.
Add sauce and lower heat to simmer for an additional hour or until slightly thickened.
Along with sauce add bay leaf, black pepper, 1 tablespoon salt and apple (sliced).

title: delicious cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons of sugar and margarine and press into bottom of a spring-form pan.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Bake cake according to cake mix directions in 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine sugar and pineapple. Bring to a boil and pour over cake while cake is still hot. Put bananas and pecans on top. Mix pudding as directed on box and pour over pecans and bananas. Add Cool Whip over pudding. Add coconut on top.

title: dill tomatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Broil tomatoes for 5 minutes. Remove and spoon mixture on top of each tomato half.

title: pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift dry ingredients.
Mix water and extracts.
Add sifted ingredients to egg mixture alternately with combined water and extracts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 375° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: peppers and cheese
directions: Drain roasted peppers; place in a bowl.
Mix with Provolone. Dress with spices and olive oil.
Refrigerate overnight or serve immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Mix in sour cream and Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers on bottom of a large bowl.
Slice 2 bananas over wafers.
Pour half of pudding over bananas.
Place another layer of wafers and bananas.
Pour remaining pudding over and top with crushed wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: ann's baked beans
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay strips of bacon on top.
Quarter hot peppers.
Lay on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie dish with apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Pour margarine over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, egg and nuts together with fork and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in preheated oven.

title: frozen cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Then fold in Cool Whip and freeze. Can be put in loaf pan or mold.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 cornbread mix, meat, corn and cheese, top with rest of batter.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown beef, rice, green pepper and onion in oil in heavy skillet.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Place sliced squash in a casserole and top with meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make a crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour and sugar together; cut in shortening.
Add yeast to buttermilk.
Blend the two mixtures.

title: cherry date cookies
directions: In a large 10-inch pan, melt butter; stir in sugar and dates. Remove from heat and add egg; beat and return to heat and continue cooking over a medium heat and stirring constantly, until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients except the 2 1/2 cups of coconut.
Stir well and let stand about 20 minutes.
You may cool in refrigerator.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.
Great for the holidays.
May be frozen and used at a later date.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: rosie's cheese ball
directions: Mix first four ingredients and form into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in pecan-parsley mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: steam barbecued corn-on-the-cob
directions: Plunge freshly picked ears of corn into large bucket of cold water.
Do not shuck or remove the silks.
Soak for 30 minutes. Place dripping ears on grill over hot bed of charcoal.
Turn often as they steam for 10 to 15 minutes.
Husks can be now be removed easily but be careful, they will be steaming hot!
Spin corn through bar of butter, salt and munch immediately.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Blend first seven ingredients in blender.
Add blended ingredients to remaining ingredients.
Chill
mixture 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with garnishes:
croutons or chopped hard-boiled egg whites, green pepper or onions.

title: simple punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Stir in ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: In large bowl, mix well the flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening until particles are fine.
Store at room temperature in large glass container with tight cover.
Use as needed.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, peel and vanilla until well blended.
Add yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cook lasagna noodles per package directions.
Mix together all cheeses (except topping cheese), egg and parsley to make filling. Place 1/3 cup filling on lasagna noodles and roll up like a pinwheel (seam side down).
Place in baking pan that has 1 cup of spaghetti sauce spread on bottom.
Continue until filling mixture is used up.
Cover rolls with remaining spaghetti sauce and 1 to 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips in a large bowl.
Add chips; fold in.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 325° for 1 hour. Cover with foil for first 30 minutes cooking time and then remove foil for the last 30 minutes cooking time.

title: sauce for green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve over green beans. Best when made a day ahead.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except stuffing and butter. Place in baking pan and top with stuffing.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy oven chicken and gravy
directions: Season chicken as preferred; roll in flour.
Place in rectangular baking pan or casserole dish.
Mix soup with 1 can of water and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Chicken will form its own crust and soup will make gravy.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: In large baking dish, layer with crackers, oysters and pats of butter to top of dish.
Pour oyster liquid and milk over all. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix together all but last 3 ingredients.
Form balls and put into casserole dish.
Pour remaining ingredients over balls.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350° or cook all day in crock-pot.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients with dry, after having sifted dry ingredients in large bowl.
Bake in 2 loaf pans (5 x 9-inch) sprayed with Pam at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: asparagus congealed salad
directions: Mix the gelatin with 1/2 cup cold water; set aside.
Mix the 1 scant cup cold water, white vinegar and sugar; let these come to a boil and set off stove.
Add gelatin to the mixture.
Hurriedly, drain the can of asparagus; mix with pimento, chopped pecans and chopped celery.
Add these to the gelatin mixture.
Let it set. Makes about 1 1/2-quart size dish.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in 1 or 2-inch pieces.
Mix flour, salt, seed, egg and water together.
Dip chicken in flour mixture.
Deep fry in oil at 375° until golden brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add liquids.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Bake for 1 hour in tube pan at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; mix well. Combine eggs, corn, milk and butter; mix well and stir in dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot vegetable oil.
Cook until golden brown; turn once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or syrup.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: decorated cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla.
Divide flour into thirds and add to batter, creaming well each time.
Knead gently until smooth, approximately 5 minutes.
Shape in ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 5 hours or overnight.
Taking 1/4 part of dough, roll out 1/4 inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Now, decorate cookies with colored sugars or sprinkles.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 dozen, depending on size of cookie cutter.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix equal parts of all ingredients.
Keep in airtight container.

title: braised cabbage and sausage
directions: If sausage other than small links is used, it should be cut into sections, 2 to 3 inches long.
Separate the leaves of the cabbage and wash; do not wipe dry, but shake the leaves lightly, leaving some drops of water clinging to them.
Rub the bottom of a heavy skillet with bacon drippings.
Put in layers of cabbage leaves, the sausages or sausage pieces buried among them.
Close the skillet tightly; cook for 20 to 30 minutes over medium coals. Test the cabbage at the thickest portion for tenderness.
Season with salt and pepper by taste, using only enough to supplement the flavor the cabbage has drawn from the sausage.

title: chicken noodle soup(low-fat recipe)
directions: Cook the first 11 ingredients 1 hour.
Skim foam.
Refrigerate chicken.
Skim fat.
Bring broth to a boil and add the remaining ingredients plus cubed chicken.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Yields 16 cups.
Contains 70 calories per cup and 2 fat grams per serving.

title: soda pop barbecued chicken
directions: Skin raw fryer; place in large pot.
Pour can of Dr.
Pepper and an equal amount of barbecue sauce over chicken.
Add salt if desired.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Turn chicken several times while simmering to make sure barbecue sauce covers well.
Ready to serve.

title: spicy mexican corn
directions: Drain picante sauce and set aside.
Add 1/2 cup water to corn and cook uncovered over medium heat.
Add drained picante sauce and bring to boil.
Put in serving bowl and add cheese.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: best scalloped potatoes
directions: Rub 1 tablespoon butter on bottom of 1-quart baking dish. Overlap potatoes in 3 layers, sprinkling each layer with a little salt.
Pour
half and half over potatoes, just enough to cover them. Dot top with remaining 1 tablespoon butter (optional).
Bake at 325°
in middle of oven for 45 minutes.

title: beef in burgundy sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion in margarine.
Meanwhile, drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to mushroom liquid to measure 1 cup.
Add to meat with gravy mix and wine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet-n-sour sausage
directions: Cook green pepper, onion and sausage 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and ginger.
Stir in vinegar.
Add soy sauce and preserves.
Stir into sausage mixture.
Heat over low heat until thickened.
Stir in pineapple; heat.
Serve over rice.

title: frosted apricot salad
directions: Drain apricot halves and pineapple reserving liquids. Add water to liquids to make 1 1/2 cups.
Chop the apricots.
Dissolve the Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add measured liquid and chill until slightly thickened. Fold in fruits.
Pour into 9-inch square pan. Chill until set, but not firm.
Blend mayonnaise into Cool Whip. Spread over gelatin.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill until firm.

title: fish fillets elegant
directions: Put all ingredients, except fish, in blender and blend 15 to 20 seconds.
Place fillets in baking dish and pour on sauce. Cover dish with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: grandma charlie's tomato catsup
directions: Mash the tomatoes through a colander.
Heat the tomato pulp and onion until boiling.
Add the dry ingredients, mixed with 1/2 cup vinegar.
Boil 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: alaskan whale stew
directions: Cut whale into bite size pieces.
Mix ingredients, except rabbit, in an olympic size pool, filled with non-chlorinated water.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer two to three days or until tender.
If it appears that the stew will not serve the entire group, add showshoe rabbit.
This requires caution, however, as some people dislike hare in their food.
Serves 5,000 to 10,000.

title: don's potato dumplings
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain and mash or force through a sieve to rice.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Turn out on floured cloth or board and knead slightly
with
flour.
Roll
into	logs
and slice into 2-inch pieces
and
form into individual balls.
Drop dumpling balls into a	large
kettle of boiling salt water.
Cover and watch for
the dumplings to rise.	After they rise, cook about 5 minutes.	Remove a	dumpling
and
slice
in
half to check doneness.
If done, they will appear dry and light throughout. If wet and spongy, cook a while longer.

title: jason's chocolate rice krispies treats
directions: In a large cooker, melt chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Stir in Rice Krispies and mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet. Place in refrigerator until hardened and sticks together.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: cream brulee
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat cream in a double boiler and stir in sugar.
Beat the egg yolks until light and pour the hot cream over them gradually, stirring vigorously.
Stir in vanilla and pour into a souffle dish.
Place dish in a pan containing 1-inch hot water and bake until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Chill.

title: yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the ingredients and pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and then turn out to cool.

title: sweet bread dough
directions: Crumble yeast into bowl.
Add 1 cup milk and 1 cup flour; set aside in warm place.
Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour and salt alternately with yeast mixture and remaining milk.
Add lemon rind.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic (15 minutes).
Set aside in warm place until doubled in bulk (2 hours).
Form into desired shapes.
Allow to rise again for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crostini
directions: Mix walnuts, cream cheese and Bleu cheese.
Spread on bread. Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes or until melted.

title: herb butter
directions: Mix all together and use on any of your vegetables or on toast.
Store in a small container in fridge.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour in casserole dish.
Mix well.
Crush 1/2 package saltine crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: favorite pork chops
directions: Shake ginger, salt, pepper and soy sauce on each side of pork chop.
Grill or bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: daphone icebox cookies
directions: Cover 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt margarine; add white sugar and egg and milk mixture.
Cook until thick.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
Spread on graham crackers and cover with graham crackers.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: In small saucepan, heat cottage cheese, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, blend warm liquid, 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda, yeast and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. By hand, stir in 1 1/2 cups flour to form a stiff batter. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in size, 45 to 65 minutes.
Grease a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole. Stir down dough.
Place in casserole. Cover and let rise until light and doubled in size, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and when loaf sounds hollow when tapped. Remove immediately from casserole. Brush with margarine and sprinkle with coarse salt.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in a 2-quart bowl on High 2 minutes; stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.

title: meatless borsch
directions: Saute onions in some oil or margarine.
Add liquids and spices.
(One tablespoon spices, bay leaves and clove of garlic in cheesecloth bag.)
Add carrots and celery; let simmer until soft. Add some sour cream and dill; stir well.
When serving the borsch, add a dab of sour cream on top.

title: homemade chili
directions: In skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is browned.
Drain. In large saucepan, combine all ingredients together and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: jenn's corn bread
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and oil.
Beat just until smooth.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: super shrimp casserole
directions: Use a greased shallow baking dish, just large enough to hold shrimp in one layer.
Arrange shrimp and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a skillet, saute mushrooms in 3 teaspoons butter until brown.
Transfer them to a bowl.
Toss the mushrooms with the flour and stir in sour cream, 4 teaspoons softened butter, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over the shrimp and sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Cook carrots.
Saute onion in butter; blend in flour.
Remove from heat and stir in milk; return to heat and thicken.
Stir in salt, pepper sauce, marjoram
and cheese.
Add carrots to sauce. Bake in casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: meringue
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Using an electric mixer, beat whites and cream of tartar in a large bowl to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar and continue until stiff and glossy.
Spread meringue over filling, sealing meringue to crust edges and mounding slightly in center. Bake until brown about 10 minutes.

title: meaty minestrone
directions: Wash kidney beans and place in Dutch oven.
Add water; bring to boil.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain tomatoes; add liquid to beans.
Add meat, cabbage, carrot, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and basil to beans.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cut reserved tomatoes into pieces.
Add tomatoes and macaroni to soup and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Bake crescent roll dough in circle pizza pan.
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix and spread on crust.
Cover with remaining ingredients.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Pour the Italian dressing over the spaghetti.
Mix. Dice the onion, tomatoes, cucumbers, peppers and celery.
Mix all together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: Wash and trim broccoli into spears.
Place in steamer basket, cover and steam 7 minutes until tender but still crisp.
Drain and arrange in serving bowl.

title: summer squash
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until just tender, about 5 to 10 minutes; drain and mash slightly, then drain again. Combine with sour cream, butter, onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered one quart casserole.
Top generously with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: coq au vin(chicken in wine)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In Dutch oven, cook bacon over medium high heat 5 minutes.
Add chicken and garlic.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned, 8 to 10 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium bowl, with wire whisk, stir together flour and chicken broth.
Add to browned chicken mixture.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover; bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 45 minutes or until carrots and potatoes are fork tender. Yields 8 servings.

title: hawaiian sunset cake
directions: In a large bowl combine first six ingredients. Mix well and pour into three greased and floured
9 inch round baking pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan. Let cool completely after you remove them.

title: sun-maid raisin nut cake
directions: Grease and flour a loaf tin, 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Sift together first three ingredients.
Add nuts.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add the flour mixture alternately with the milk, beating well after each addition.
Bake in the prepared loaf pan in a moderate oven (350°) for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes, stirring until cubes are dissolved.
Combine cornstarch with small amount of bouillon mixture, blending to a smooth paste.
Stir into remaining bouillon mixture.
Add corn syrup, meat, soy sauce and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add green peppers to meat mixture and cook an additional 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add blueberries and pineapple (including juice).
Let set and jell.
With mixer, blend cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add sugar.
Stir in nuts and spread on Jell-O.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Gel slightly.
Cream cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Slowly add Jell-O.
Add pineapple (do not drain).
Add 7-Up and gel until set.

title: black-eyed pea spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain and set aside. Cook peas according to directions and drain and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings in large skillet until onion is tender.
Add beef and cook, stirring constantly, until browned. Drain off drippings.
Add next 10 ingredients, mixing well. Simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in spaghetti and peas; simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Following directions on package, make 1 large cookie, using pizza pan or biscuit pan.
Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip and add confectioners sugar.
Spread over cooled cookie.
Sprinkle with flaked coconut.
Add crushed pineapple (drained), kiwi fruit and sliced strawberries or other fruit.
Peaches and bananas are a nice combination.
I only use 1 to 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar.

title: south-of-the-border oven barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Place chicken in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Brush chicken with barbecue sauce. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with green chiles and chopped green bell pepper. Bake 15 minutes more or until chicken is done. Place chicken on a serving platter, reserving drippings. Stir drippings until smooth and pour over chicken. Top with cheeses. Serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: hot slaw
directions: Mix liquids in large pot; bring to a boil. Mix the rest of ingredients together. Pour in hot liquids; boil for 5 minutes. Put in jars. Put jars in big pot. Cover with water. Bring to boil. Boil for 5 minutes to seal jars. This is good with hot dogs and barbecue.

title: spicy christmas tea
directions: In a large mixing bowl, pour two parts canister mixes to one part cinnamon, until one or more ingredients is gone.
Mix everything well.
Pour even amounts into sandwich bags and close with a twist tie.
Store in a cool, dry place.
If you desire to give as gifts, you may wish to place bags into small gift bags. Be sure to include the service directions.

title: easy sour cream cucumbers
directions: Combine onion and cucumbers.
Stir together sour cream, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Toss with vegetables; cover and chill, stirring occasionally.

title: caramel popcorn and peanuts
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in heavy 2-quart saucepan. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda. Pour a steady stream of syrup over popped corn and peanuts.
Mix well.
Put in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes. Store in airtight container.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: Brown meat; remove fat.
Drain on paper towels.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook 8 hours on low or 6 hours on high.
Serve over fluffy rice or chow mein noodles.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Turn into shallow buttered casserole.
Mix cheese and chips and spread over top of casserole.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: red devil franks
directions: Cook onion and garlic in margarine over low heat until onion is tender, about 10 minutes. Stir frequently. Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, sugar and chili sauce. Continue heating until flavors are well blended, about 5 minutes. Split frankfurters lengthwise and arrange split-side up in shallow pan. Spoon sauce over frankfurters and heat under broiler until frankfurters are hot and sauce is bubbly, 3 to 5 minutes. Serve hot on split, toasted buns. Spoon on extra sauce.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss bread crumbs with butter in bowl.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, whipped topping and pudding mix. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in thirds.
Mix pineapple juice and almond extract and drizzle over cake.
Cut lengthwise.
Spread 1/3 pudding mix over bottom layer of cake. Top with second layer.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding. Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted, sliced almonds.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Heat and stir into gelatin.
Add pineapple tidbits and pecans.
Gradually stir in ice cream until melted and blended.
Chill.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, parsley, onions and seasonings.
Add rice and shrimp; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Slightly crush corn flakes.
Combine with melted butter and almonds; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Finely chop tomatoes, onions and jalapenos. Pull cilantro from stem or chop and add to vegetables. Toss with salt and a few drops of lemon juice.

title: can can chicken
directions: Mix soups, chow mein noodles, evaporated milk and chicken. Put into a greased baking dish.
Cover with cornflake crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip with pudding.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Set aside.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Combine with first mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts. (Secret:
Use your hand to squeeze apples through mixture.
This makes a big difference.)
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 325°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: texas goulash
directions: Saute onion; add beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Very cheesy and kids love it!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add vanilla, oil, sugar and squash.
Mix lightly. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.
(Can also make muffins out of this.)

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Soak peeled rind overnight in a gallon of water with lime. Wash and boil in slightly salted water for 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Boil sugar, vinegar, spices and rind and cook for about 1 hour.
Fill jars and seal.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix salt, yeast and sugar. Add warm milk and shortening. Gradually add flour until dough holds together. Knead well. Put in a large, greased bowl. Cover with waxed paper or small towel. Sit in warm place until dough doubles in size. Remove dough from bowl. Punch down and knead well. Roll out on counter. Knead more. Spray several 8-inch pie plates with Pam. Shape dough into medium egg-size balls. Place in greased pie plates (approximately 7 balls per plate). Let rise until doubled in size in a warm place. Bake at 375° approximately 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Stir in salt, pepper and flour.
Heat; add meat, vegetables, tomato sauce, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Roll biscuit dough 1/4-inch thick for top crust and cover.
Fill with 2-inch biscuits.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain and chill.
Add rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: no bake pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk as directed on box.
Blend in margarine and fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust or ready made crust.
Chill and serve with whipped topping if desired.
Pudding can be any flavor and you may use fruit layered on crust if desired.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt and margarine.
Cook at Full power 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Add soda and vanilla.
Place popcorn in large paper grocery bag and pour mixture over corn.
Stir with wooden spoon to coat corn completely.
Cook at Full power 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag.
Repeat, but shake bag every 30 seconds to check for doneness.

title: hot potato dish
directions: Pick a large bunch of poke greens; wash well.
Put into a large pot and cook for 20 minutes.
Pour off water.
Add more water and boil for 20 minutes longer; drain.
Fry 6 slices of bacon until done and remove from pan.
Add greens to pan with bacon grease. Cook about 15 to 20 minutes; salt to taste.
Add 4 or 5 beaten eggs and stir until eggs are done.
Good with cornbread.
Place bacon slices on side of bowl and eat with the greens.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in salt water.
Put in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over wings in container and cover. Refrigerate overnight. Place chicken in shallow pan. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces. Marinate in sherry or white wine for 30 minutes.
Drain before cooking.
Steam broccoli 1 1/2 minutes and rinse under cold water.
Mix together water, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Saute chicken in oil 2 to 3 minutes. Add cornstarch mixture and vegetables; cook 3 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: round steak en casserole
directions: Have butcher tenderize round steak.
Cut into serving-size pieces.
Flour steak pieces with flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Brown in hot oil quickly.
Place meat in casserole.
Add water to skillet and stir to form thick gravy.
Thin gravy with water.
Pour over meat, cover and bake.
oven cook meat, covered, 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with fork.
When it is done will be very tender.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Use pineapple juice and cold water to make scant cupful.
Put into blender.
Add cream cheese. Beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Mix with spoon.
Pour into mold of choice.
Refrigerate until set.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water.
Cream sugar with melted margarine and add beaten egg.
Add yeast, flour and mix well.
Drop into well-greased muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes. Dough may be keep in refrigerator until used.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: family quickie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and melt margarine in the oven in Pyrex bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and add milk. When butter has melted, pour batter on top.
Do not mix!
Pour in pie filling.
Do not mix!
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: spaghetti squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Prepare baking dish (8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch) by greasing lightly.
Lightly toss spaghetti noodles with milk and egg.
Spread evenly in baking dish.
Spoon sauce over to and place pepperoni slices over sauce followed by cheese sprinkled on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and chicken.
Mix well. In baking dish, place layers of tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients in large covered skillet or saucepan. Stir occasionally until comes to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; cover with ice cubes and let stand 1 hour.
Rinse well.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Add vegetables and cook for 4 minutes.
Put in jars and pour liquid over; seal.

title: crock-pot pork barbecue
directions: Put 1/2 onions in bottom of crock-pot.
Add meat and ingredients with remaining onions on top. Cover and cook overnight on low heat (about 8 to 12 hours).
Remove bone, onions and fat from meat.
Pour off liquid from the night cooking.
Cut up pork butt into small pieces.
Add large chopped onion and 16 ounces barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook 1 to 3 hours on high or 4 to 8 hours on low. Stir 2 or 3 times during cooking.

title: peas 'n' corn
directions: Drain liquid from peas and corn.
Simmer 15 minutes to reduce liquid.
Add rest of ingredients and heat.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar and beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, reserved liquid, thawed strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with various fresh fruits. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dry orange jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle dry jello over and refrigerate overnight.

title: old-fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Mix seasonings together and sprinkle over bread cubes. Add onion mixture and water. Combine. Stuff rinsed turkey and roast immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put 1/2 dressing in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup and cream, then add squash, onions and softened margarine.
Pour in casserole dish and put rest of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: war cake
directions: Boil raisins and water or coffee a little.
Add shortening while raisins and water are still hot.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(Mom said that this was made often during World War II.
The ingredients were more easily found during rationing and only a little sugar was needed.)

title: broccoli tuna roll-ups
directions: Cut broccoli spears in 1-inch pieces.
Combine soup and milk. Set aside.
Combine tuna fish, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Stir in 3/4 cup soup.
Divide tuna mixture evenly between the tortillas and roll up.
Place seam side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir tomato into remaining soup and pour over top of tortillas.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top center of tortillas with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: cocktail sandwiches
directions: Cook hamburg and sausage; drain off grease.
Add cheese and seasonings; mix well.
Spread on bread, after cutting off crusts. Prefreeze on cookie sheets for 5 minutes.
Freeze in individual packages.
When ready to use, cut in 4 pieces.
While frozen, broil about 3 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and onion in water until almost soft.
Drain, then add cheese, mayonnaise and 3/4 of bacon.
Mix together and put in a casserole dish.
Next, top with rest of bacon, crumbled. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites in a medium mixing bowl until very stiff peaks form.
Add sugar gradually while beating on slow speed.
Fold in vanilla, chocolate chips, nuts and salt. Line cookie sheets with aluminum foil and drop by teaspoon.
Place in oven and turn oven off.
Leave in oven for 6 hours or overnight.
Do not open oven during this period.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Combine all, but topping ingredients, into a small saucepan and slowly melt, stirring constantly.
Pour into a bowl and chill until firm.
Using a melon baller, shape into balls and roll into topping mixture.
Place on plate and keep in refrigerator.
Set at room temperature approximately 30 minutes before serving.

title: sandra's cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in an ungreased skillet. Add remaining ingredients except crumbs to meat; mix well. Pour into casserole dish and top with crumbs. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Fry chicken breasts in butter.
Salt with garlic salt while frying to taste.
Remove chicken from skillet and cut into bite-size pieces.
Add milk and can soup to remaining butter and make a gravy.
Put pieces of chicken back into skillet and mix well.
Cook rice by directions on box.
When done, put rice on bottom of casserole and chicken mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry tall cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions for 2 layer cake; cool completely. Slice the layers in half and place in freezer. Slice strawberries and mix with the strawberry glaze. Reserve 3 tablespoons of the mixture for the top of the cake. With a mixer, beat cream cheese, granulated sugar, whipped topping and powdered sugar until well blended. On a serving platter, place a halved layer of the frozen cake. Spread a thin coating of the cream cheese mixture on the layer; then cover with 1/3 of the glaze mixture. Repeat process with 2 more frozen halved layers. Place the remaining frozen halved layer on top and cover top of cake with the cream cheese mixture. Place the reserved 3 tablespoons of glaze mixture in the center of the cake and decorate with the whole strawberries.

title: pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayo, mustard, vinegar and spices. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and toss well to coat.
Cover and chill several hours before serving.

title: coconut rolls
directions: Roll out the dough to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Warm butter or margarine in the bottom of a baking pan.
Spread some of it on the dough.
Follow with brown sugar, then coconut.
Roll up.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Dip in the oil in the pan, then turn so it has a buttered top.
Raise to a desired height and cook according to the roll recipe.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Cook diced eggplant in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Combine with other ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 4-6.
Tastes like oysters.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil fryer, then debone.
Add rice to 2 cups broth.
Can add more rice to more broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked hamburger
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, milk, onion, salt and pepper. Make into patties and fry nice and brown.
Make sauce of catsup, sugar, mustard, vinegar and 3/4 teaspoon salt; pour over patties. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in covered dish.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well and spread mixture into ungreased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: rolled meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into any Bisquick mix as for biscuits or bread mix.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is done at 350°.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions for 7 minutes; drain. Add all ingredients.
Save some cheese for top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sesame bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake until center is set, about 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars (2 x 1-inch).
Makes about 6 dozen bars.

title: garlic bread
directions: Spread butter on bread.
Sprinkle on garlic.
Put into preheated oven at 325°.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add wafers, bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into muffin pans.
Makes about 24 muffins.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir until onion is tender.
Crumble bacon; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for about 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, sour cream, onion, soup and egg.
Melt butter and mix with dressing.
Mix 1/2 of dressing mixture with first mixture and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add strips of cheese on top of mixture.
Add remaining dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven-fried tomato slices
directions: Preheat oven to 400° in shallow dish.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, oregano, pepper and garlic.
Mix well.
Coat tomato slices evenly with crumbs.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick vegetable spray.
Place tomato slices on baking sheet.
Drizzle evenly with margarine.
Bake about 5 minutes until tomatoes are tender.
Heat broiler.
Place tomatoes under broiler and broil for 2 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with the apricot tapioca pudding.
Set aside.
Boil the jello, sugar and pineapple until dissolved and then cool.
Add apricot mixture to the boiled ingredients.
Add Cool Whip.
Do not drain the pineapple before cooking it.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and hot water. Mixture will be very
thick.
Make corn pones or drop 1 tablespoon batter in hot grease.
Brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: best-ever chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease and flour a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Put flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Cook margarine, cocoa and water, just until mixture comes to a boil. Cool 1 minute.
Pour mixture over flour and sugar while beating with electric mixer.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla. Beat 1 minute more.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Frost while hot with Best-Ever Chocolate Icing.

title: pecan crust cheesecake
directions: Press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Thaw, drain and pat dry spinach.
Mix all ingredients, then refrigerate.
Great with celery, carrots, cauliflower, chips, etc.

title: mom's eggless milkless cake
directions: Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes the sugar, shortening, spices, salt and water.
When cool, add the flour, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon-ginger flip
directions: For each serving, mix fruit juices in a glass and sweeten to taste.
Fill glass half full of crushed ice.
Add ginger ale and top with shredded lemon peel.

title: venison parmesan
directions: Marinate meat in marinating sauce and Italian dressing overnight in bowl, turning periodically.
Bread meat in bread crumbs and flash fry in hot skillet, using a small amount of olive oil.
Layer fried meat in bottom of a medium size casserole dish. Cover with a layer of spaghetti sauce and cheese in between each layer of meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: sausage bits
directions: Soften cheese in microwave and mix well with sausage and Bisquick.
Make into small balls and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
May be reheated in microwave.

title: scallops in garlic butter
directions: Cut scallops in half; soak them in milk for 10 minutes.
Drain and dry on towel.
Dust scallops lightly with flour.
Heat butter in skillet.
Add garlic and stir.
Add scallops and saute until lightly brown and just heated through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in parsley and serve at once with lemon wedge.

title: cheese cloud pie(sugar-free)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in reserved juice until smooth. Beat in pudding mix and salt.
Fold pineapple and Cool Whip into cheese mixture.
Put in crust and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: peach cheesecake
directions: In blender, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over water; let stand 2 minutes.
In small saucepan, bring juice to a boil; add juice to blender at low speed until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and process at high speed until blended.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch prepared crust.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with peaches.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake covered for 45 minutes.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and brown.
In saucepan, bring water to a boil; add rice and soup mix.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Add celery, onions and peppers to sausage.
Cook until tender.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish and top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry
directions: Brown meat in 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil in large, deep skillet; drain.
Add vegetables of your choice with 1/4 cup water to meat.
Cook until tender, stirring to keep vegetables from scorching.
Serve on top of cooked rice.
Season with soy sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Season with salt and pepper; mix cream of chicken soup, 1/4 cup chicken broth, and milk.
Pour over chicken, separate from bone.
Saute celery and small onion in margarine. Add cornbread stuffing mix, egg and 1 1/2 or 2 cups chicken broth. Add on top of soup mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in a covered casserole at 350°; then 15 minutes uncovered.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin pie mix, flour, eggs and condensed milk in large bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour over top the cake mix and pecans.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes exactly.
So good, so rich!

title: hot dog stew
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook at low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (preferably the day before it is to be served).
Before serving, add 1 can of drained peas and heat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie(serves 2)
directions: Mix all ingredients and then add beaten eggs.
Put into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until pies "set".
Makes 2 pies in 9-inch pans.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cook broccoli until stems are "almost" tender.
Line broccoli in baking pan.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Top with layer of crushed crackers, Town House or Ritz (prefer Town House), then top with tabs of butter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Line an 8 x 10-inch pan with crushed graham crackers mixed with melted butter.
Mix together pie filling, pineapple, condensed milk and whipped topping.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: spam casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles; saute Spam, onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Add soup and stir.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli and rice together with other ingredients.
Cook in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: the world's best buffalo wings
directions: Heat oil in a 3 quart pan or larger at 375 degrees.
Wash chicken wing pieces.
Drain chicken and fry until crispy.
Place chicken on paper towels for excess oil drainage.
Place chicken in large bowl and pour in 2 Tbsp. of Texas Pete sauce.
Mix well, adding sauce if desired for hotter wings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine pineapple, water and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add jello.
Let cool and add the cream cheese, nuts and celery.
Mix until cream cheese is mixed in.
Refrigerate until slightly thick.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: white frosting
directions: Cream the egg white and shortening with electric mixer.
Add vanilla or almond extract, sugar and milk; beat until smooth and creamy.
Makes enough to frost a large layer cake. Sets in seconds and refrigerates well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together).
Add apples and nuts.
If stiff, add 1/4 cup buttermilk.
Bake
in 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium sized electric mixer bowl, combine baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
In a small bowl, mix together melted butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm. Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend the cream cheese, eggs and sugar together.
Add the cornstarch, vanilla and sour cream.
Pour into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Leave in oven for 1 hour with door open.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese eggs
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray.
In a large bowl beat eggs with fork.
Pour in skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
When done, turn off heat and add cheese.
Place lid on skillet for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons(makes approximately 3 dozen)
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Blend egg whites and almond extract.
Blend coconut mixture into egg whites.
Drop onto prepared cookie sheet.
Top each macaroon with half of a maraschino cherry.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bass with bleu cheese sauce
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, mix flour and sour cream.
Blend in wine, cheese, chives and white pepper.
Cut fish into serving size pieces; place in prepared pan.
Spread with sauce.
Bake until fish flakes at thickest part, 30 to 40 minutes.
Place fish on warm serving plate.
Stir sauce before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Quarter zucchini lengthwise and cut into small pieces. Combine with onion, boil for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix other ingredients, except for stuffing, into zucchini and onion mixture. Melt margarine and mix in stuffing.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Combine only half of the stuffing now and use the remaining half as a topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water; add frozen strawberries and then stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into dish.
Let set.
Add Cool Whip.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk.
Boil this mixture only one minute.
(You may simmer two minutes on very low heat.)
Have ready, vanilla, rolled oats and peanut butter.
Stir this into boiled mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: yule chiffon cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth with a spoon.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until whites form very stiff peaks. Do not underbeat.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten egg whites.
Gently fold just until blended; do not stir.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain, squeezing out excess liquid.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: prize coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour an oblong pan.
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in milk; blend in remaining dry ingredients.
Spread batter in pan.

title: kraut casserole
directions: Mix vegetables and pour sugar over vegetables.
Set aside. Heat vinegar, oil and water until boiling.
Pour over vegetables and set in icebox and let set for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cabbage-macaroni casserole
directions: Boil cabbage with carrots 7 to 10 minutes. Drain. Make sauce of flour, butter, salt and milk. Slice cream cheese and add to hot sauce.
Lightly mix vegetables, macaroni and sauce together. Spoon into baking dish. Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook and stir until blended and hot.
Serve in chafing dish with chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Add together tomatoes with zucchini, squash and onion that have been cubed and parboiled.
Layer in baking pan with Ritz cracker crumbs, top with cheese and pour Milnot over top. Microwave on Medium (1/2 power) for 20 minutes total or bake.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Stir together salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put cooked macaroni in casserole.
Add tuna in chunks and chopped eggs.
Dilute the soup using 1/2 can water.
Add to macaroni and tuna and stir.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in
1 gallon freezer container.
Freeze until firm.
Let ripen at least 1 1/2 hours to develop flavor.
Enjoy!

title: mixed herb spaghetti and clam sauce
directions: Heat tomatoes, tomato juice, wine, lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper to boiling in Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in parsley, basil and clams.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Stir in butter.
Add sugars, eggs, flour, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Bake in a well-greased 11 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a a 1 1/2-quart shallow dish, melt oleo.
Sprinkle in crumbs.
Stir well.
Press in bottom of dish. In medium bowl, mix condensed milk, sour cream and lemon juice. Spread evenly over crumbs.
Spoon pie filling evenly over creamed mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Mix nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in a large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts (batter will be stiff). Drop by heaping teaspoonful about 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 9 1/2 minutes or until browned. Yields 4 1/2 dozen cookies, 2 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: apple dumplings(easy)
directions: Roll biscuits out.
Put in about 1 tablespoon chopped apples. Fold and seal edges.
Put into a baking dish.
Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour this syrup over the dumplings.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, egg yolks, salt, milk and sugar in saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, and beat until stiff peaks are formed. Spread over cooked filling.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool before serving.

title: chicken pillows
directions: Open crescent rolls; using 2 triangles, press 2 edges together to form a square.
Mix chicken, cream cheese, sour cream and garlic.
Place spoonfuls of mixture in center of square.
Divide filling for 8 servings.
Fold edges of roll together to form pillow and squeeze edges to seal.
Mix melted butter with crushed croutons and sprinkle on finished pillows.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; beat in eggs and add milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Last, add mashed bananas.
Can use vanilla (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mixed as directed.
Add smashed clove of garlic.
In a separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and grated Parmesan cheese.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Place in layers in a large baking dish:
noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese slices and meat sauce.
Repeat. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve with garlic bread and a garden salad.

title: sally lunn
directions: Add sugar, salt and butter to milk.
Cook to lukewarm.
Add yeast, eggs and flour.
Beat well and cover.
Let rise in warm place until double (about 2 1/2 hours).
Stir down and pour into well-greased pan or baking dish.
Cover and let rise again until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 375°
for about 45 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot with plenty of butter.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Mix together milk, juice and Cool Whip.
Then add fruit to this mixture and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Makes one deep dish pie or two smaller ones.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: healthy choice oriental stir-fry
directions: In large skillet or wok, heat salad dressing, soy sauce and ginger.
Quickly saute peppers until almost crunchy-tender.
Add onion and cover, cooking for 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat, stirring in snow peas and tomatoes.
Serve over fluffy white rice.

title: asparagus with ginger and sesame
directions: Bring about one cup of water to a boil in a skillet large enough for the asparagus to fit completely inside.	Add asparagus; cover skillet and boil for 3 to 5 minutes.	Drain and quickly cool to room temperature or less.

title: delicious dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients in bowl until smooth and creamy.

title: pizza
directions: Place yeast in large bowl and add lukewarm water; stir to dissolve.
Add sugar and salt and place in a saucepan with fat or oil.
Add milk; scald and add flour, one cup at a time.
Dough will be soft.
Grease cookie sheet or 2 pie pans and spread very thin coat in bottom of pan.

title: creamy banana pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in the milk and egg yolks; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in softened gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Cover the surface of custard with plastic wrap and chill until no longer warm.
Slice 3 bananas; fold into custard with whipped cream.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until set, about 4 to 5 hours.
Shortly before serving time, place lemon juice in a small bowl and slice the remaining banana into it.
Melt jelly in a saucepan over low heat.
Drain banana; pat dry and arrange on top of pie.
Brush banana with the jelly.
Sprinkle with grated lemon peel.
Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: laverne's never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together all ingredients; roll on floured surface adding flour as needed.
Store remaining in refrigerator until needed. Or place in pie plate and freeze until needed.

title: beef parmesan
directions: Trim meat and cut into serving size pieces.
Pound to tenderize and coat with flour.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip meat into egg, then into crumb and cheese mixture. Brown meat in cooking oil, then place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: homemade bisquick
directions: Mix well and store in tight container.

title: irish soda bread(a much lighter recipe - original recipe)
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil. Remove from stove and add 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda and let stand for 1/2 hour. Drain water out.

title: applesauce pecan cake
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving:
Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Reserve 18 pecan halves for garnish, chop remaining pecan halves and set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add applesauce and next 6 ingredients, and 1 teaspoon salt.
At low speed, beat until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake cake 35 to 40 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
