Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes and remove cake from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: tuna stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove centers of mushrooms carefully.
Finely chop stems.
In a frying pan, cook stems in butter; add tuna.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add onion and seasonings.
Remove from heat.
Stuff caps with mixture. Place in a greased baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes until brown.
Yields 12 appetizers.

title: corn crispy fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken, pat dry.
Mix corn flakes, flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then dip and cover well with corn flake mixture.
Melt butter in shallow pan, place skin side down in melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, bake 15 to 30 minutes more.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook oleo, sugar, eggs and dates in heavy skillet about 20 minutes or long enough to cook eggs.
Add vanilla, nuts and cereal.
Stir.
Form balls and roll in nuts or coconut.
(I like nuts better.)

title: pavolova
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat until stiff enough to stand in peaks.
Place mixture on well-greased slide or ovenproof plate and bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 230° for 1 hour.
Leave in oven to cool. Decorate with whipped cream and fruit.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In pan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of prepared pie shell.
Pour filling over bananas.
Cover. Chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream; garnish with remaining banana slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: brie in puffed pastry
directions: Slice Brie in half horizontally.
Place almonds in equal layer. Reassemble cheese.
Thaw pastry shell for 20 minutes.
Set cheese in center of rolled pastry shell (must be in 15-inch circle). Brush edges with egg.
Pull up to top.
Place seam down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush top with egg wash.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Great on butter crackers.

title: hominy salad
directions: Cook hominy. Cool. Add other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the sugar, water, syrup and salt to a hard boil, 250°. Add the butter and the Spanish peanuts.
Cook to a golden brown. Remove from heat and add the vanilla and soda.
Spread on buttered pans.

title: memere's biscuits a melasse(or grandma's molasses cookies)
directions: Sift the following dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, ginger, allspice and salt.
Put oil, sugar, molasses, water and 1 egg in blender.
Combine dry ingredients with liquid mixture and drop by tablespoon or teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen large cookies or 30 average.

title: no cook flour icing
directions: Blend together.
Beat on high speed for 10 to 12 minutes. Can add peanut butter.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine
corn
with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking
dish.
Bake
in
a 325° oven for 45 minutes or until firm and lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk.
Bring to a medium boil, to a soft ball.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Put beef in 8-inch square casserole. Pour pizza sauce over ground beef and top with cheese.
Add oregano and basil.
Mix Bisquick mix, milk and eggs together.
Beat until smooth. Pour over cheese and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese.
Add sour cream.
Mix in sugar and pie filling alternating with milk.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.
Top with cherry or your favorite pie filling before serving.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown
pork
chops
in
shortening.
Arrange
in baking dish. Cover with chicken gumbo soup mixed with the 1/2 cup of water. Bake in 350° oven at least an hour.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven
to
Butter
a 6 cup mold or baking dish. Mix
all ingredients.
Pour into prepared dish and bake 3 1/2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes for the first 2 hours. Bake until rice is very tender.
Serves 8.

title: glorified potatoes
directions: Grate cheese and mix with potatoes (thawed or frozen). Heat margarine, soup and sour cream until bubbly and mix with potatoes and cheese. Place in large casserole dish. Add enough milk to cover 3/4 to 1 cup. Dot rest of margarine on top. Top with Special K cereal or crumbs (corn flake, bread, etc.) If potatoes are thawed thoroughly, bake at 350° for 30 minutes. If frozen, bake 1 1/2 hours or until bubbly.

title: onion cheese ball
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cheeses, onion and Worcestershire sauce until well mixed.
Shape into a ball and roll in parsley.
Chill and serve with crackers.
Makes one 4-inch ball.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup of hot water and juice from cherries.
Let set.
Whip and add cherries, cottage cheese and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold.

title: caramel-pecan pinwheels
directions: Combine caramel topping and butter; pour into a lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Separate breadsticks but do not uncoil; place on caramel mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; let stand 3 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter; let stand 2 minutes.
Remove pan and serve immediately.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well in bowl and serve with fresh cut fruit.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° or 2 hours at 275°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornmeal and cocoa in bowl.
Add eggs, butter, corn syrup and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and milk.
Mix together flour/sugar and egg/milk mixtures.
Add margarine, cook on medium heat until thick, stir constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 400° until meringue is brown.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on bottom.
Thoroughly combine strawberries with syrup with dry gelatin; set aside.
In a large bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Blend on low speed until well moistened. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter over marshmallows. Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar and mix. Add 4 eggs and mix.

Sift flour, cocoa and salt; add to margarine, egg and sugar mixture. Add vanilla. Mix well. Mix by hand (add nuts if desired), do not use electric mixer. Pour batter into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. After brownies cool, ice with Betty Crocker's milk chocolate RTS frosting.

title: pineapple whip pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool at least 1 hour.

title: the topping of choice
directions: Melt the chocolate first.
Put the chocolate in a bowl then crush the almonds and mix them in the chocolate.

title: swirl
directions: Put vanilla ice cream in a bowl.
Put the chocolate syrup on the ice cream.
Swirl the ice cream and the syrup together.
Add the banana with the ice cream and eat right away.

title: pizza burger
directions: Open buns.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Spread meat on buns; top with cheese.
Toast under broiler.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well; roll in chopped pecans.
Makes 1 large or 2 small balls.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar, flour and chopped nuts together. Spread into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pat down.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool; crumble with fork.
Pat down again.

title: cheezy chowder
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water; add potatoes, mixed vegetables and onion.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until Cheez Whiz is melted and chowder is hot.
Makes six (1-cup) servings.

title: nutty noodly clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in noodles and nuts until evenly coated.
Dip out by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate and chill.

title: colorado cache chicken salad
directions: Combine dressing ingredients (mayonnaise, vinegar, soy sauce, onion and curry powder).
Chill for several hours or overnight. Toss dressing with chicken mixture (first 6 ingredients).
Chill. To serve, spoon onto pineapple slices arranged on lettuce leaves. Serves 6.

title: bundt cake
directions: Keep butter at room temperature until soft.
Separate eggs. In large bowl beat egg whites with 1 cup of sugar until fluffy; set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
To soft butter add egg yolks and remaining sugar; beat well.
Gradually add flour by 1/4 cup at a time.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Gently mix with egg whites.
Pour mixture in 9-inch Bundt cake pan. Warm oven for 5 minutes at 350°.
Place cake in oven; cook for 90 minutes.
Check with knife.
When well done, cool and remove from pan.
Sprinkle top of cake with confectioners sugar.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: With mixer, beat sugar, eggs and bananas. Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Trace of fat.)

title: caviar and salmon spread
directions: Mix the cream cheese and cream or milk gently.
Stir in scallions, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
Fold in the smoked salmon and caviar until well combined.
Be careful not to overmix so the shreds of salmon and caviar can remain whole.
Serve with crackers or toast points.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: cream cheese delights
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread 1 package crescent rolls in a 9 x 13 pan for crust.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crust.
Put other package of crescent rolls on top.
Beat egg white slightly and spread on top of rolls.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased pans at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast speciality
directions: Butter one or both sides of bread.
Cut in cubes and lay in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle cooked sausage over bread cubes. Grate cheese over sausage.
In a bowl, combine eggs, half and half, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Mix at slow speed until well blended.
Pour over other ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes in the morning and do not drain.

title: baked corn
directions: Place corn in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to milk with the eggs.
Pour over the corn.
Dot with the butter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crepes
directions: Beat eggs without separating.
Mix sugar, salt and flour well together and stir quickly into eggs.
Add milk and beat hard. Pour just enough butter to cover bottom of lightly greased pan when tilted and swirled.
Shake crepe over until slightly brown on bottom and firm to touch on top (dull look).
Do not turn over. Put aside to cool.
(May be done hours ahead.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the margarine, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
With fork dipped in flour, flatten in crisscross pattern to 2-inches.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not hard. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Add 2 eggs, alternating with flour, then add other eggs.
Place in cold oven. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Do not open oven.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease large baking sheet. Sift flour and salt.
Rub in butter until mixture looks like bread crumbs.
Then add sugar and raisins.
Mix to a soft dough with milk.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Put on baking sheet. Brush with milk.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with jam and tea. Makes 12.

title: pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice as thick as you like.
Put back into jar.
Slice garlic thin and add to sliced pickles.
Simmer the sugar, vinegar, cloves and cinnamon for 5 minutes until clear and hot.
Pour over pickles.
Cover jar tightly and leave sealed for ten (10) days.
(Important: Do not open any sooner than 10 days.) Very tasty for all occasions.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend milk, flour, margarine, onions and bouillon cubes.
Pour over chicken. Spread mushrooms over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.
A family favorite.

title: pears and cream tart
directions: In small bowl, mix cinnamon, nutmeg and 3/4 cup sugar; set aside.
In another small bowl, with wire whisk or fork, beat cream with egg yolks until blended; refrigerate.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Rub dish or enamel pan with crushed garlic (and throw away). Warm wine in enamel pan or chafing dish.
Shred or grate cheese; mix with flour.
When melted, add seasonings and Kirsch.
Add by handfuls to warm wine slowly (so not to curdle cheese).
Serve with pieces of French bread (or on toast).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Scrape mushroom caps.
Wash. Chop stems and onions.
Saute in butter until browned.
Mix rest of ingredients with sauteed mushroom pieces in a bowl until thick, but moist.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cashew tuna bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir until onion is tender. Reserving 1/4 cup chow mein noodles, stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle reserved chow mein noodles over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: rio grande buttermilk
directions: Place frozen lemonade and tequila in your blender.
Fill with cracked ice and blend.
Serve in salt-rimmed glasses, if you desire.

title: sticky cinnamon buns
directions: Arrange rolls in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle dry powder of butterscotch pudding over rolls.
Melt butter; add cinnamon and brown sugar to sugar; drizzle butter mixture over top.
Let set on counter, covered, 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. This is good to make the night before.
You go to bed and pop in the oven when you get up in the morning.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place croutons in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread sausage over croutons.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, soup, onions and mushrooms.
Pour over sausage, croutons and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large pot, brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper; saute for a few minutes.
Add chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste and ground cumin.
Stir until chili powder is evenly coated over contents.
Add tomatoes, Veg-All, Ranch Style beans and water.
Bring to a boil; turn down and let simmer about 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold in 1 package pistachio pudding mix.
Let set overnight.

title: easy cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip (optional).
Pour into crust.
Put lines of chocolate sauce across pie (optional).
Use knife to pull through lines to decorate. Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: chocolate slush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese (room temperature), confectioners sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over cool crust.
Beat 2 packages instant chocolate pudding and 3 cups milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread more Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Partially bake pie shell, approximately 10 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar well; beat in egg yolks, one by one.
Beat in flour and buttermilk.
Add lemon juice and nutmeg with a pinch of salt.
Whip the egg whites stiff and fold into the filling.
Pour filling into partially baked pie shell and bake in the middle level of the oven until the custard has set and is slightly browned, about 1 hour.

title: faren's yummy milkshake(this recipe is for 1 serving)
directions: Pour milk into blender container.
Add ice cream, jam and pudding mix.
Cover tightly; blend until mixed well.
Pour your milkshake into a tall glass and enjoy.

title: slavic cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and blend well.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Put half batter in greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread apricot filling over this.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Take from oven and cool. Cut in inch square pieces.
May be sprinkled with powdered sugar. Store in tight container.

title: pumpernickel bread(with potato; 3 loaves)
directions: Combine the whole wheat and rye flours.
In a very large bowl, mix 2 cups of the flour mixture with the salt, cornmeal and yeast. In a saucepan, heat the water, molasses, cocoa mixture and butter until very warm (about 120° to 130°).
Add this to the dry ingredients in the large bowl.
Add the mashed potatoes and 1 more cup of the flour.
Stir in caraway seed and enough of the flour mixture to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead for 15 minutes.
Add more flour if the mixture seems too sticky.
Place in a buttered bowl; turn once to coat top.
Cover and place in a warm spot to rise until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Heat milk in saucepan, but do not boil.
In a bowl, mix the sugar, cocoa, flour and salt and stir in enough milk to make a smooth paste.
Pour this into the warm milk.
Stir continuously over moderate heat until the sauce thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve over hot, buttered biscuits.
Serves 4.

title: iron skillet pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple; save 2 tablespoons syrup.
Melt butter in 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Stir in brown sugar until blended. Remove from heat.
Arrange pineapple slices in sugar.
Place a maraschino cherry in center of each slice.

title: yum yum spice cake
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil all ingredients, except the flour mixture.
After mixture has cooled, add flour and soda; blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam (glass pan if you like).
Spread apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly; spread over apples.
Place pats of butter over top.
Bake until topping is golden, about 30 minutes.

title: nanny craig's russian salad
directions: Mix jello, water, cream cheese and marshmallows over low heat until dissolved.
Let cool, then add remaining ingredients. Congeal.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meats and save broth.
Cook onions and pepper together and save broth.
Grind meats after they cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at low heat, stirring frequently as this burns easily.
For storage, cool before putting into freezer cartons.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cranberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Let chill until slightly thickened.
Break cranberry sauce up and stir into the gelatin. Add chopped celery and nuts.
Pour half the mixture into mold or dish and spread evenly with the sour cream.
Pour remaining cranberry sauce mixture over top and chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jeremy's tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix soup and meat until soup is heated throughout.
Pour into nonstick dish and top with a layer of Tater Tots.
Cook casserole according to directions for oven prepared Tater Tots.
Top with grated cheese.
Very easy and can be doubled or tripled for a large dish.

title: french crisps
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and flour.
Spread thinly on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt one large chocolate bar and spread on cookie immediately after removing from oven.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Cut while warm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix by package directions with additions of 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 (6 ounce) package coconut.
Bake by package directions in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 13-inch pan.
Meanwhile, heat together but do not boil the milk, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stick cake with wooden toothpicks to make holes.
Pour hot mixture over cake.
Allow milk to run into holes.
Let cake cool completely.
Spread thawed whipped topping over top of cake and sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter (or use Pam cooking spray) 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. With an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs, beating well. Stir the dry ingredients together and combine with the butter mixture. Blend well. Add the bananas, sour cream and vanilla. Stir well. Stir in the nuts and chocolate chips and pour into the pan. Bake for 1 hour, until a cake tester comes out clean. Turn onto a rack to cool.

title: janet gardner's salad dressing
directions: Put first six ingredients into blender for approximately 5 minutes; first on low, then on high.
Turn blender back to low and pour oil in very slowly.
Cover and return to high blend for another 5 minutes.
Makes 3/4 quart.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and nuts (optional).
Mix well.
Form into balls and place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: stuffed italiano green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove stems and seeds.
Parboil in salted water; drain.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Place paper liners in muffin tins and put 1 vanilla wafer in each.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice. Beat egg whites with salt until peaks form. Fold egg whites into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into muffin tins until 3/4 full. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool in paper liners by chilling several hours.
Remove papers.
Top cheesecakes with your favorite preserves.
Peach, strawberry or raspberry are all good.

title: apple cake
directions: Don't use mixer.
Stir up.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter raisin log
directions: Blend honey and peanut butter. Gradually add dry milk; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Shape into a 12-inch roll. Wrap tightly. Store in refrigerator.
To serve, cut into slices.

title: hot creamy beef dip
directions: Finely chop dried beef.
Beat cheese and sour cream together until light and fluffy.
Stir in beef, onion and seasonings.
Turn into a shallow baking dish; top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: mushroom and celery stir-fry
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet, then stir-fry chopped celery.
Add sliced mushrooms.
Sprinkle with garlic and onion salt to flavor. A quick, easy vegetable.

title: german chocolate dump cake
directions: Combine pecans and coconut.
Place in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour cake mixture over top of pecans and coconut.
Combine butter or margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls over top of cake mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Put bacon drippings in pan or dish; add sugar and cornstarch. Blend well; stir in salt, pepper and vinegar.
Heat on medium until thick or microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until thick.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Add green beans, wax beans, red kidney beans and onion slices to mixture, stirring well; cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Sprinkle cooked bacon pieces on top and serve.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: wall plaque
directions: Blend salt and flour in a bowl, adding water a little at a time.
Knead dough 7 to 10 minutes, until firm.
Place in plastic bag to keep from drying out.
Form into any shape.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until hard (test for hardness by tapping with spoon).
When cool, paint with water colors or food dye, if desired.
Varnish to protect from moisture.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs until smooth.

title: surprise casserole
directions: Cook noodles in 3 quarts boiling water until tender.
(Add 1 teaspoon onion salt and 1 teaspoon oil to water.)
While noodles are cooking:
Mix together 1 teaspoon onion salt, celery flakes, parsley flakes and soup with half of the milk.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix the flour, 2 cups of sugar, eggs, orange juice, oil, vanilla and baking powder, one at a time, to make batter.
In a separate bowl, mix the apples, 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon. Using a Bundt cake pan, layer batter, then apples and repeat layers until all batter and apple mixture is used.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: creamy chicken lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, add mushrooms and onion; cook until tender, stirring occasionally. Add cream cheese and bouillon.
Cook until cheese is smooth and bouillon dissolves, stirring often.
Remove from heat, stir in sour cream, eggs, nutmeg and chicken; mixing well.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and chill 30 minutes or more. Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Make 1-inch balls from dough and roll in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Bake, 2 inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: everyday cake
directions: In an 8-inch pan, stir all ingredients with rubber spatula until well blended.
Scrape down sides of pan.
Bake according to directions.
This has 190 calories.
Serve with fruit or whipped cream.

title: barbecued beef with rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer on low heat until onion and celery are tender.
Brown 1 to 1 1/2 pounds chopped beef (bite size) and cook either in crock-pot or skillet until tender.
Cook rice (at least 2 to 3 cups).
Place on serving dish (in center). Place meat around rice and pour sauce over meat.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: In a flat pan, layer the following:
first layer is lettuce; second layer is celery; third layer is onion; fourth layer is green pepper or water chestnuts and fifth layer is peas.
Mix sugar with mayonnaise and pour over the above layers.
Sixth layer is cheese and seventh layer is the bacon bits sprinkled on the top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green and red pepper jelly
directions: Combine sugars and vinegar in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add peppers; boil 15 minutes. Let stand for 2 hours. Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: fennel and garlic crusted pork loin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
On cutting board, combine garlic, fennel seed, salt and pepper.
Chop together to break seed and mince the garlic.
Rub mixture over surface of pork.
Place in small roasting pan.
Add chicken broth to pan.
Roast pork 50 minutes or until meat thermometer reads 150° and center is pink, but cooked through.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cauliflower and broccoli in 3-inches of boiling water in large saucepan.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Drain.
Over medium heat, melt together milk, Velveeta (in chunks), 1/4 cup butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Add the vegetables; cover and stir often to form a cheese sauce.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spoon vegetables and cheese sauce into dish.
Arrange cheese slices across top.
Crush crackers in small bowl.
Melt the other half stick of butter.
Pour over cracker crumbs and stir in.
Sprinkle this across top of casserole and bake 20 minutes.

title: summer hacienda dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, salsa and onion salt until well blended. Spread cheese mixture in microwavable pie plate or bowl. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring every 2 minutes.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
4 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until very light; add beaten yolks, water, soda, spices, preserves and flour.
Stir all together.
Beat thoroughly; cut and fold in the beaten whites. Bake in a loaf in a moderate oven about 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with plain icing.
Use blackberry, strawberry or raspberry jam.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Put rhubarb in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and jello.
Put marshmallows on top of this.
Make up cake mix as per directions.
Pour over marshmallows.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes and invert onto a cookie sheet or whatever it will fit.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 12 ounce bag chocolate chips and spread over top.
Refrigerate until hardened. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Not necessary to keep in refrigerator after cut.

title: coke or dr. pepper salad
directions: Use juices (heated) to dissolve jello and combine all the rest.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat the egg; add milk, shortening and canned corn.
Add dry ingredients sifted; beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat. Cook until golden brown.
Takes about 3 minutes to fry with frying temperature at 380°.
Makes about 16 fritters.
(Serve hot with maple syrup.)

title: squash souffle
directions: Boil squash in salted water; drain and mash.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Pour onions and butter into squash.
Add celery seed, pimentos, cheese and eggs. Mix all and bake in a buttered pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Mix ingredients well.
Drop by soup spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Remove from sheet; cool thoroughly.
Frost with frosting made with powdered sugar, oleo and orange juice.
Makes lots of cookies. Freezes well.
Kids love them, also husbands.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let cool to room temperature.
Stir in yogurt and pineapple (do not drain pineapple).
Pour mixture into a 9-inch square pan and sprinkle with walnuts.
Cover and freeze 8 hours or until set.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings, 110 calories.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening (cut shortening in). Add buttermilk and yeast (dissolved in warm water).
Work dough. Pinch off amount needed; roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Refrigerate rest and pinch off as needed.

title: ginger chicken stir-fry
directions: In a 10-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry chicken until browned and no longer pink.
Remove; set aside.
In same skillet in remaining 1 tablespoon oil, stir-fry vegetables and garlic until tender-crisp.

title: hamburger hobo stew
directions: Drain off fat from meat.
Heat all ingredients into big pot over medium heat.
When it is hot, it's ready to eat.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: mustard slaw(makes 12 servings)
directions: In a medium bowl, whisk the Dijon mustard, sugar, dry mustard, 1 teaspoon coarse salt, the cayenne and white and black peppers. Whisk in the mayonnaise.
(The dressing can be refrigerated, covered, for up to 2 days.)

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one by one and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk or juice to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° in greased cake pan for about 40 to 50 minutes or in layer tins for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box adding 1 teaspoon of coconut flavoring.
When cake is done, punch holes in top while still hot pour 1 -1 1/2 c. of cream of coconut over top, letting it soak in.
Top with cool whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: hawaiian creme cake
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together and let stand for 15 minutes.
Mix in Cool Whip and pineapple.
Blend well.
Pour in pie shells.
Chill.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour, sugar, yeast and water.
Stir well.
Add shortening, egg, salt and remaining flour.
Cover for 30 minutes in bowl.
Stir down and put in muffin pan.
Let rise.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut in bite size pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add onion and peas.
Blend soup and milk; pour over the chicken.
Mix stuffing according to package and put on top. Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water; stir 3 minutes.
Add ice; stir 3 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and whip together.
Add strawberries. Stir.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (use 325° if using glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter and press firmly until spread evenly over pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut and nuts on top evenly.
Press down gently.
Pour can of condensed milk evenly on top, then bake 30 to 40 mintues or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Loosely cover any leftovers.

title: pumphrey cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well.
Beat eggs and add to first mixture.
Add flour and salt.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easiest tangy spaghetti
directions: Fry the ground chuck in frying pan.
Heat Prego.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Continue heating.
Boil water of angel hair spaghetti noodles.
Cook according to package directions.
Drain pasta.
Top with Prego mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange tomato slices in large shallow baking dish.
Top evenly with cheese and bread crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle the herbs over all. Bake uncovered for about 1/2 hour or until cheese melts and everything is bubbly and delicious smelling.

title: pear conserves
directions: Put all through food chopper and cook one-half hour or until transparent.
Stir while cooking to keep from burning.
Put into pint or half-pint jars.
This conserve is very good when used as a cake filling.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts.
Add soup to oleo.
Melt sour cream with soup; pour over chicken breasts and top with crackers and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: super duper potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Chill potatoes 48 hours.
Remove skins and grate potatoes.
Heat margarine, half and half and salt in a 3-quart saucepan until margarine melts.
Mix together with grated potatoes and cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle grated cheese over top for last 15 minutes.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Score steak on both sides in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Marinate in other ingredients for 8 hours in refrigerator.
Grill to desired degree of doneness.
Slice across grain into thin slices.

title: baked sweet onions
directions: Core a large sweet onion for each serving needed.
Add salt, pepper, 1 bouillon cube and a generous pat of butter to hollow. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of onions.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Blend room temperature cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: layered taco salad
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, crumble beef.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cover.
Microwave at High (10) for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Add chili beans.
Re-cover and microwave at High (10) for 5 to 6 minutes, until hot.
Keep warm.
In a 2-quart casserole combine sauces.
Microwave at High (10) for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Place all ingredients except evaporated milk into pot.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are almost tender.
Add evaporated milk and simmer an additional 1/2 hour.
May top with chopped chives, if desired.

title: green beans with tomatoes
directions: Wash, trim and cut beans to desired size.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 5-quart pan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent sticking or scorching.
Remove from heat, gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into two greased 13 x 9-inch pans. Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion, covered, in small amount of water until tender.
Drain well and mash by hand. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Return to low heat and simmer just until hot. Do not boil!
Can sprinkle parsley over top for garnish.

title: squash muffins
directions: Drain any excess liquid from squash.
Combine squash, eggs and butter; stir well and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add squash mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Prepare limeade with water in a large pitcher. Stir in cranberry juice and instant breakfast drink. Pour over ice cubes in tall mugs or glasses. Garnish each with a sprig of mint.

title: easiest and best cheesecake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pat in baking pan and bake until done, not too hard (watch closely).
Cool.
Blend eggs, sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and whipped cream.
Spread onto graham cracker crust.
Spread with fruit filling cherry, blueberries, peach, strawberry.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and Parmesan in margarine until cooked down.
Add 1 can tomato sauce.
Layer Mozzarella cheese on top until it melts.

title: cheese balls
directions: Put aside 1 cup of dried beef.
Mix ingredients together and form 2 balls.
Roll balls in remaining 1 cup of dried beef.
Can freeze up to 12 months.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix as regular cake.
Beat with a mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Mix all together; simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: tuna-rice special casserole
directions: Put rice, bouillon cubes, water and seasonings into heavy 3 quart saucepan.
Add celery, olives, green pepper, mushrooms plus liquid and tuna.
Cover tightly and bring to boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon yogurt pie(low-fat)
directions: Fold thawed Cool Whip into yogurt.
Spoon the mixture into the pie crust. Refrigerate or freeze for later use.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Mix dry ingredients.
Coat chicken in plastic bag.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn.
Bake until done, about 15 minutes.

title: quiche muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix cottage cheese with mixer until smooth.
Process egg whites until foamy.
Add eggs, buttermilk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in cheese, onions and bacon.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: summer fruit punch
directions: With waxed paper, line 13 x 9-inch baking dish; place in freezer until very cold.
Using an ice cream scoop, make balls from sherbet and arrange in single layer in baking dish.
Cover tightly and freeze until hard.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Leave cheeses set out overnight.
Mix well and roll in chili powder.
Makes 2 to 3 good-sized balls.

title: tangy pineapple chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with thyme, salt and pepper.
In a skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving the juice.
Cut pineapple rings in half and set aside.
Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons juice until smooth; set aside. Combine mustard, honey, garlic and remaining pineapple juice; mix well.
Add to pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken juices run clear. Remove chicken and keep warm.
Stir cornstarch mixture and add to pan; bring to a boil.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Return chicken to pan.
Top with pineapple and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and oil. Fill greased baking pan and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato sourdough cinnamon rolls
directions: Divide dough in half.
Roll each portion into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread each rectangle with 1/4 cup of softened butter to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/4 cup raisins.

title: crab stuffed eggs
directions: Remove egg yolks from whites.
Mix yolk with crabmeat.
Blend in a mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Stuff egg whites. Garnish with pimento or parsley.

title: cranberry bread(christmas favorite)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add shortening to dry ingredients.
Mix until resembles corn meal.
Add orange juice and rind.
Stir until well mixed, but not beaten; add berries and nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Slice zucchini, add onion and pepper; saute in small amount of oil, until tender.
Pour into casserole dish.
Beat eggs, mix in sour cream and salt, pour over first mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese, return to oven for 10 more minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Bake cake by instructions on box.

title: corn balls
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Set aside to cool.
In a bowl, combine croutons, corn, eggs, water, salt, pepper, and onion mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into 8 to 10 balls.
Place in an ungreased shallow baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
This cake freezes very well.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt with shortening and sugar and cream well.
Cream egg yolk, lemon juice and vanilla and mix with strawberries.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of cookie dough on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: connie's corn casserole
directions: *Can use 2 (11 ounce) cans Mexicorn whole kernel corn, drained, to replace the 16 ounce can of whole kernel corn.
Adds color!

title: chocolate chip-peanut butter torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Break up dough into ungreased 9 or 10 inch spring form pan. Press in bottom to form crust. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.

title: garbage dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; put on plate or platter with small side.
Dice the onion, tomato, black olives and cheese; put on top of first ingredients.
Serve with any firm chips, like Tostitos or crackers.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine, oil, marshmallows and caramels in a large pan over low heat.
It will be brown and similar to marshmallow treats in texture.

title: cabbage 'n potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into chunks.
Place them in a large Dutch oven.
Cut cabbage into quarters; place on top of potatoes. Add bacon drippings.
Add water until it is over top of cabbage. Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until potatoes are done.

title: simple homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: In a blender, mix the syrup, condensed milk, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream maker container.
Pour in 2% milk (may not take all if container is not large enough).
Stir to mix the milk, then make your ice cream.

title: harriett's stew
directions: Start cooking meat in covered pan, you want some liquid from meat.
Season with garlic powder to taste while cooking.
Heat water in pan after meat is done; scrape pan into stew.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix thoroughly.
Add mix to milk in saucepan over low heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Serve over biscuits.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix well.
Place in well-greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix milk and sugar in a boiling pan.
Bring to a boil; let boil 1 minute.
Add chocolate squares.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and salt.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts sauce.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve on ice cream, cake, etc.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplants.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain.
Saute onions, garlic and parsley in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add eggplant, thyme, salt and pepper.
Work in moistened bread and slightly beaten eggs.
Fold in shrimp and crabmeat. Remove from heat.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs, butter and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and mold.

title: dill chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix all but cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: beef-potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
In casserole dish arrange celery, pepper, onion and potatoes.
Cover with meat mixture. Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepperoni mini rolls
directions: Keeping two crescent rolls together to form a rectangle, press center edges together.
Cover with 10 slices pepperoni, pressing lightly into dough.
Top with 1 1/2 slices cheese.
Roll up tightly, lengthwise.
Cut into 6 to 8 individual pieces, depending on size you want.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown in oven temperature given on crescent roll package.
Excellent!
Makes 24 to 32 individual rolls.
Can be baked ahead of time and microwaved to reheat.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Remove from stove.
Add soup, broccoli, rice and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix batter in bowl (sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk).
Pour batter over melted margarine.
Pour peaches over batter in pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: plain pound cake or christmas light fruit cake
directions: For
Fruit
Cake:
Use	as much fruit as you like, also nuts. A knife will not cut through almonds.

title: bean salad
directions: Pour over beans.
Let stand 1 day before serving.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix together in order listed.
Needs to be soupy.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Cook sausage, onion and pepper together in a skillet until sausage is browned. Mix with all other ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Pour into a greased 11 x 13 pan. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt and milk; heat until butter melts and set aside.
Mix yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let rise until bubbly.
Add to first mix.
Beat eggs well and add.
Mix enough flour to make a soft dough (do not knead).
Let rise 3 hours or overnight.
Knead down and shape into rolls.
Let rise 1 hour, no more.
Bake at 450°.

title: mother's ice cream(6 quarts)
directions: Heat milk
and	add eggs.
Stir while eggs are cooking. Mix flour with	a
small
amount
of
hot
milk
and then stir mixture into
milk	and stir while heating.
Add sugar and set off stove to	cool.
If there is time enough, place in refrigerator overnight
to
cool.
Add
vanilla.
Pour into 1 gallon hand-turned
ice
cream
freezer and layer crushed ice and ice cream
salt around bucket until freezer is full.
Freeze until too hard to turn and cover with old newspaper and plastic bag.

title: amaretto french toast
directions: Place the French bread slices in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Mix together well the eggs, salt, brown sugar, almond extract, amaretto, nutmeg and heavy cream.
Pour over the French bread. Cover the pan and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning fry in butter on griddle over medium heat and serve with maple syrup.

title: mama's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs; drain and set aside.
In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lime juice, vegetable oil, mustard, salt and celery seed; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
If desired, serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with reserved green pepper.

title: braised peppered moose steak
directions: Grind up leftover steak or roast.
Grind raw potato and onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
Fry until hot and add leftover gravy if too dry.

title: corn cheese bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Stir well. Pour in a hot greased pan. (A No. 6 skillet is good to use if you have one.) Bake in 400° preheated oven about 30 minutes or until brown. Yields 8 servings.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Drain and mix green beans and corn.
Put in casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and salt. Spread over bean and corn mixture.
Melt margarine.
Add in Ritz crackers (crushed) and almonds.
Spread on top of casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: jan metcalf's broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Blend oil, vinegar, paprika, onion powder, celery seed and salt.
Let set 1 hour.
Cut vegetables into bite size pieces. Pour dressing on salad vegetables and let set 1 hour refrigerated. Stir when ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon, then add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in greased bread pan.

title: chicken rotel
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine. Add onion and bell pepper. Saute.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add tomatoes and chicken. Mix well and add egg noodles.
Stir.
Pour into large casserole dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: big soft pretzels
directions: Lightly grease 2 large baking sheets.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Blend in 4 eggs and slice margarine.
Add 10 cups flour, sugar, salt and nonfat instant milk.
Stir well. Add additional flour to make a soft, but not too sticky dough.
Knead 5 minutes, until dough is smooth.
Roll pieces of dough in ropes, about 1/2-inch in diameter and 18 to 24-inches long.
Form into pretzel shapes.
Place on baking sheets.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Place in cold oven.
Bake 1 or 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: irish oatmeal muffins
directions: Bake a yellow cake in a rectangular pan.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix and gelatin together.
Add eggs, oil and wine.
Blend to moisten.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from pan and let cool.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Lay the peas out to thaw.
Chop cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Dice all other ingredients fairly small, except peas.
Mix all vegetables and water chestnuts together, then add peas.
Pour Hidden Valley Ranch or Seven Seas Caesar Dressing over vegetables.
Let marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: bologna salad
directions: Grind bologna and cheese into large bowl.
Add all other ingredients and stir.

title: italian sausage and potatoes
directions: Mix and arrange ingredients in a long, shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn and baste every 20 minutes.

title: spicy rice vegetable casserole
directions: Heat slowly together to prevent burning (stir often) the butter or oil, onion, green pepper, garlic and the rice.
Slice and stir into mixture the carrots and celery.
Season with thyme, oregano, salt and pepper.
Place vegetables and rice in a large baking dish.
Pour 3 1/2 cups boiling water over the blended mixture; stir thoroughly.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: In
a
food processor or blender, process cookies until crumbly.
Mix
in
melted butter.
Pat mixture into bottom and sides
of
a
9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Spread softened ice cream
over
crust.
Pour a generous amount of fudge sauce and marshmallow cream over ice cream.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Repeat layers:
chocolate, ice cream, fudge sauce, marshmallow and nuts.
Chill
for
at
least 3 hours.
Remove from freezer for 10 minutes before serving.

title: crock pot hamburger stew
directions: Place layers of vegetables, in the order given, in the crock pot.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the browned ground beef on top of the celery.
Mix the tomato soup with the water and pour over this.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. You can cook on high for 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: In glass pie
plate
or casserole, heat butter 30 to 45 seconds.
Add
milk or water and eggs, blending lightly with a fork.
Cover
and cook as following, stirring one or two times during
the
last
half of cooking time: 1 egg - 30 to 45 seconds; 2
eggs - 1 1/2 minutes; 4 eggs - 2 1/2 to 3 minutes; 6 eggs -
to 4 1/2 minutes; 8 eggs - 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from
oven,
stir and rest 2 to 3 minutes, covered.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pizza breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fold dough and press out bubbles. Knead for a few minutes.
Stretch and pat dough onto pizza stone. Dough may resist stretching but eventually relax.
Cover dough and allow to rest for 15 minutes.
Pat and stretch dough over sides of stone (will shrink back a bit).
Brush dough with olive oil. Press garlic cloves with press and spread over dough.
Grate Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese over dough.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown. Use pizza cutter to cut in long strips and serve with pizza sauce for dipping.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Requires a lot of mixing.
Roll into balls and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: taco lasagne(372 calories per serving)
directions: Cook lasagne according to package for 10 minutes; drain. Separate lasagne and lay flat on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep the pieces from sticking together as they cool.
Meanwhile, brown beef, onion and green pepper in 10-inch nonstick skillet; drain off excess fat.
Stir in taco sauce, water, salt, pepper, basil and chili powder.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: special potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, 1 cup cheese and sour cream together. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° (uncovered).
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top 10 minutes before potatoes are done.

title: apple rolls
directions: Use enough milk to make a soft dough. Roll out. Spread with butter and apples. Roll up again and cut into pieces. Pour hot syrup over pieces and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grape juice crush
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Serves 30.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack in jars.
Put 1 pepper, 1 clove or garlic in each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Pour over okra and seal.
Makes five pints of delicious okra.

title: sangria blanco
directions: Cut several end slices from fruits.
Keep the center of fruit for slicing later.
Place the end slices in a small saucepan with water and sugar.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Lower heat and simmer, undisturbed for 3 minutes to make a simple syrup.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.
Strain the syrup; squeeze juice from the fruit. Discard the cooked fruit end slices.
Chill the syrup, covered, up to 1 week.
On day of serving, thinly slice center of fruits, discard seeds, chill fruit slices, cover until ready to use.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put all together in a bowl and mix well with hands.
Roll into balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue pork and beef
directions: Combine ingredients in a 3 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 8 hours.
Stir mixture with wire whisk during cooking time, until meat is shredded.

title: creamy beef and noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain, rinse and set aside.
Crumble ground beef into 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole. Add onion and garlic.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring once.
Stir to break meat into pieces. Drain.
Stir in tomato paste, water, salt, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture boils and flavors are blended, stirring once. Set aside.
Beat egg in 4-cup mixing bowl.
Beat in mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Fold in noodles.
Spoon evenly over meat mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until noodles are heated, rotating dish once.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
To serve:
Mix 3/4 cup hot water with 3 tablespoons cocoa mix.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cook ham bone in water to cover.
Cut ham from bone.
Add 2 quarts of water to ham broth and add all the other ingredients. Cook for 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned gumbo
directions: Use equal parts of peanut butter, chocolate syrup and light Karo syrup.
Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Take 1/2 pint jar and put some in it, leave out of refrigerator so you will have some ready to use.
Very good.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use with Fritos "Scoops" corn chips.

title: dandelions with bacon dressing
directions: Wash and thoroughly drain dandelion stems.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Pour off fat, except 2 tablespoons.
Blend flour into these 2 tablespoons fat and gradually add water.
When thoroughly mixed, add beaten egg, salt and vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over dandelions and serve at once.
If desired, dandelions may be cooked slightly and drained well before adding sauce.

title: pork with green beans and mushrooms
directions: Slice and prepare all ingredients as for stir-fry.
Place oil in wok or Dutch oven; heat to medium heat.
Add pork and onion; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce, beans, salt and 3/4 cup water. Cover wok or pot; cook for 6 minutes on medium high.
Lift cover several times to stir so all will be cooked thoroughly.
Add mushrooms; cook for 3 minutes, covered.
Stir twice.
Mix cornstarch in 1/2 cup water; add to other ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes to thicken.
Shut off heat and serve.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: louisiana pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: In medium size bowl,
combine
butter, sugars and salt; blend well.
Add eggs, one at
a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla,
flour,
cream
and
pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell.	Bake in
moderate oven at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until
knife
inserted
near center comes out clean.
Serve slightly warm with whipped cream.

title: herb roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place potatoes on baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.
Using hand, toss to coat evenly.
Season potatoes with salt and pepper.
Bake 10 minutes.
Using spatula, turn potatoes.
Toss with herbs and garlic and bake until potatoes are golden and tender, about 13 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: In a large kettle, heat oil and saute onion, celery, garlic, green pepper and carrots.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, seasonings, shrimp and scallops.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 to 60 minutes.
Add wine and crabmeat.
Warm only.
Serves 6.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Mix
and bake cake mix according to package directions. Heat sugar,
milk
and
marshmallows
until
melted.
Stir in coconut and spread over cake.
Heat sugar, Pet milk and butter or margarine
to
a
boil.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips. Spread on cake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together the first seven ingredients and set aside.
Brown ground meat; drain on paper towel.

title: too good to be a dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. And serve.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water, oleo and oatmeal together; let stand about 20 minutes.
Mix brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour, soda and salt together with spoon.
Add oatmeal mixture and mix with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and Bisquick in large bowl.
Add just enough water to make workable.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients and put into a 9 or 10-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes; cool completely and top with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: strip and go naked(sheraton-biloxi)
directions: Shake and pour over ice. Top with beer.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze dough.
When you are ready to bake the cookies, break off pieces of dough and shape into small balls (about the size of a large grape).
Place on greased baking sheet. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven about 13 minutes.

title: gram's cheese straws
directions: Mix cheese, butter and salt (if used) together.

Adding flour as needed, work in enough to make a stiff dough (use your hands to mix). Roll out on floured board to about 3/8-inch thick. With sharp knife, slice into strips about 3/8 x 4-inches. Sprinkle with red pepper. Bake in a 350° oven until slightly brown. (Use a very lightly greased baking sheet.) When cool, remove from pan. Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add hot water, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut in squares.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip and coconut.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Saute celery and onions in butter. Add cheese and soup and stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Yields 3 cups.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: You will need a deep fryer or deep frying pan.

title: cotton pickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and juice from oranges.
Add oranges and pecans.
Bake in three pans at 350° until brown.

title: tuna delight
directions: Combine tuna with undiluted soup and green beans.
Brown Tater Tots in oven, then place on top of casserole.
Bake at 300° until mixture is bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: tipsy pork chops
directions: Melt butter and fry chops on both sides.
Remove and spread the mustard on one side.
Keep warm.
In the remaining butter and juices from the chops, fry the chopped onion and stir in the flour. Add the herbs and cider and cook until the sauce thickens.
Place the sliced apples in a casserole and pour the sauce on top of them. Place the chops on top and brown in the oven at 350° or gas mark 4 for 25 minutes.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, pecans and flour.
Mix well.
Shape into balls using about 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie. Bake at 300° on ungreased baking sheet for about 45 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot and again when cooled.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: double cheese noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together (except grated cheese.
Save that for last and sprinkle on top) in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: special occasion breaded corn
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix corn, green pepper, salt and beaten eggs.
Pour half of mixture into buttered 3-quart casserole dish. Crush a few crackers over top (thin layer); dot with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Slowly add remaining corn mixture.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top; dot with butter and sprinkle generously with cheese.
Slowly pour milk over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle paprika over top to add color before serving.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, eggs, pecans, coconut, raisins and vinegar, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pastry shells. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes, stirring 20 minutes after casserole has been cooking.

title: manicotti
directions: Pancakes:
Combine flour, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Beat until smooth. Add 4 eggs (one at a time).
Heat a 5 to 6-inch skillet that has been greased with a drop of oil.
Put in a small amount of batter and roll. Cook until firm.
Flip.
(Use a Teflon pan.)

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients slowly (low heat) until it thickens. Great over ice cream.

title: special k bars
directions: Grease a mixing bowl.
Put Special K in it.
Bring sugar and Karo to boiling point.
Blend in peanut butter.
Pour over Special K; mix well.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Melt the chocolate chips, adding a little milk, if needed.
Spread over mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir all together and put into a 9 x 13-inch casserole or large round casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 generously.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Mix strawberries, sugar and liqueur in a large bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla ice cream.
Spoon into serving dishes and serve at once.

title: fat free zesty garlic dip
directions: In blender, blend cottage cheese, lemon juice, milk, paprika and garlic until smooth.
Stir in scallions.
Chill 1 hour to blend flavors.
Garnish with paprika, if desired.
Serve as a dip with pretzel chips.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: mixed fruit punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or more.
Pour mix through a wire mesh strainer into a large bowl.
Discard mint.
Stir in ginger ale and next four ingredients.	Add ice.
Makes 5 1/2 quarts.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix
together first 10 ingredients.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch
baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly
browned.
Immediately
sprinkle with chocolate pieces on top;
allow
to
melt,
then
spread over top.
Mix last 3 ingredients and drizzle over chocolate.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Make sauce first.
Mix sugar and flour well, add water.
Mix well.
Add food coloring, then cook until thick.
Cut rhubarb and put in bottom of well-greased pan.
Pour sauce over top of rhubarb.
Then top with topping.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite chips. Also freezes well.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat the eggs with the sour cream.
Sift together the sugar, flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Stir the cream and eggs into the flour mixture.
Flavor with vanilla.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix All-Bran, bran, water and raisins.
Let stand 2 minutes; add vegetables, sugar, eggs, salt, soda, flour and buttermilk. Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Keeps up to 6 weeks; cover well and refrigerate.

title: march family pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: linguine salad
directions: Note:
Chop as much as you want of tomatoes, onions, celery, green pepper, pepperoni, Provolone cheese, black olives and salad olives.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and pour on water.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and sprinkle on top of the apples.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sheepherder's dip
directions: Cut a 5 to 6-inch circle off the top of bread.
Pull out soft insides (save for dipping).
Soften cream cheese.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Fill shell with mixture.
Replace top of bread.
Cover bread with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Use fresh vegetables as well as top of bread for dipping.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: "impossible" coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy tortilla pizzas
directions: Sprinkle cheeses on 2 tortillas and top with a second tortilla.
Spread top with tomato paste and sprinkle with oregano and other favorite pizza spices.
Sprinkle on more cheeses and top with mushrooms, black olives or other favorite toppings.
Make one "pizza" per person.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 10 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in the juice drained from the can of pears; add crushed pineapple.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese in the milk and mix until smooth and gradually add the cream cheese to the gelatin mixture.
Stir in the horseradish sauce.
Cool in refrigerator until partially set.
Add the pineapple and chopped pecans.
Whip the cream and fold gelatin mixture into the cream. Put in mold and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Serve.

title: wheaties cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Add milk and coconut and stir.
Then add Wheaties, nuts and vanilla, stirring after each addition.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and put in refrigerator to set.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips or onion rings.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle chips/onion rings on top.
Return to oven and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: depression cake(eggless, milkless, butterless cake)
directions: Put the ingredients in a saucepan and boil for 5 minutes. Cool.
Add 2 teaspoons of soda in 1 tablespoon warm water and 3 cups of flour.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 1 1/4 hours. Top with Cool Whip or whipping cream.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs on high for 1/2 minute.
Add sugar and salt to eggs.
Continue beating on high for 1/2 minute.
Stir in milk and vanilla on low for 1 minute.
Pour custard into buttered custard cups or 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Set cups or casserole in shallow pan.
Add water, enough for 1/2-inch depth.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 custard cups.

title: russian tea
directions: Add orange juice, lemon juice and sugar to tea (which you have already made with 2 quarts of water).
To this add cinnamon and cloves (which have been tied in cheesecloth).
Bring to a boil, turn down to simmer.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove bag with spices.
Add pineapple juice.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, heat it up.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Line a 12
x 8 x 3-inch pan with half the wafer crumbs. In a bowl,
cream
the
butter and sugar well.
Add the beaten eggs one at
a
time; mix well.
Spread batter over the crumbs in the pan. Be
sure to seal well so the pineapple juice will not drain through.
Drain
the pineapple and add to the cream which has been
whipped.
Spread
this over the butter layer. Sprinkle chopped
nuts over the cream layer.
Top with remaining wafer crumbs.
Let
stand in refrigerator 24 hours, or at least overnight before serving.

title: sorghum cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Roll in balls in palm of hand (grease palm of hand) size of a large hickory.
Dip and roll in sugar.
Do not flatten.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: baked haddock
directions: Place fish in greased baking dish.
Cover with cream of shrimp soup and the canned shrimp.
Spread the butter or margarine over mixture.
Cover with the crushed Ritz crackers.
Spread finely chopped onion over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use large microwave bowl.
Pour sugar in bowl; put cocoa, milk and oleo on top of sugar; do not stir.
Cook on High power for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer until thick and creamy.
Pour in greased dish; cool.
Cut in squares.
You may add pecans if you wish.

title: caramel pie
directions: In skillet, saute 1/2 cup sugar until brown.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, milk, egg yolks and flour.
Cook until thick.
Add brown sugar, slowly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour into pie.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: championship dip
directions: Mix ingredients. Chill until ready to serve. May add crab, lobster or shrimp.
Makes 30 servings.

title: aunt rolene's steak
directions: Sprinkle round steak with garlic salt and pepper to taste. Cut steak in serving pieces and roll in flour.
Fry in a little oil to brown.
Remove steak, add 3 or 4 tablespoons of flour to skillet to soak up grease and brown slightly.
Add 1 cup water and 1 can of tomato paste or sauce, celery, onions and mushrooms.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Cook spinach; press out moisture and chop finely.
In skillet, saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until golden.
Stir in spinach.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer 1 hour.
Makes enough sauce for 3 to 3 1/2 pounds of pork, beef or chicken.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail and mix with apples and bananas.
Add walnuts and Cool Whip.
Stir walnuts and Cool Whip into fruit.
Use only enough Cool Whip to mix fruit.

title: red devil's food delight
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and cocoa. Add shortening, milk, vanilla and food coloring. Add unbeaten eggs. Beat 2 minutes. Pour in greased pans and bake at 350°. When cool, frost with desired icing.

title: farm style oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in water.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.
Contains 65 calories each.

title: delicious punch
directions: Combine all ingredients into large punch bowl; mix well. Serve!

title: orange julius
directions: Fill blender with ice and whip.
Great for breakfast!

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla together until fluffy.
Add flour and mix until combined.
Stir in (crush in bag) potato chips.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Set aside. Combine in large mixing bowl the soup, eggs and mayonnaise. Blend in 1 package of cheese. Fold in broccoli. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Sprinkle top with other package of cheese. Melt butter in saucepan. Mix in stuffing mix until well coated. Sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: scallop broil
directions: Rub the bottom and sides of a shallow baking dish or pie pan with the garlic; add half the melted butter and swish around. Arrange the scallops in the dish, season with salt, pepper and a little cayenne.
Dust slightly with flour and paprika.
Pour remaining butter over scallops.
Cook under boiler for 10 minutes or until golden.

title: you can't beat a burger
directions: Combine tomato sauce, sugar and oregano in a small saucepan. Reserve 1/3 cup of mixture; set aside.
Cook remaining mixture over low heat, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat and keep warm.
Combine beef, 1/3 cup reserved sauce, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into 6 patties about 3/4-inch thick.
Place burgers on the rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes on each side or until burgers reach desired degree of doneness.
Place patties on bottom half of buns; top each with a slice of cheese, onion and pickle.
Broil until cheese melts.
Spoon sauce over patties and cover with top half of buns.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg, stirring well.
Combine 1 1/3 cups flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice; add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in applesauce. Dredge pecans and raisins in remaining flour; stir to coat well. Fold into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan before cutting into 3-inch squares.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: lemon meringue pudding
directions: Beat 3 egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar until light.
Then fold in juice and rind of lemon.
Simmer in double boiler until thick. Beat 3 egg whites stiff; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Gradually fold egg whites into egg yolk mixture.
Chill and serve topped with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: the colonel's banana punch
directions: Using a 6-quart or larger vessel, make a simple syrup by dissolving sugar in water.
Add all other ingredients, except ginger ale.
(Mash bananas at the last minute, as they darken quickly.)
Pour mixture into freezer containers and freeze.
To serve, thaw and add ginger ale to make slush.
(Thawing doesn't take long, since mixture does not freeze to a solid.)
Makes about 40 half-cup servings or 5 quarts.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Boil until clear.
Put just a few drops of yellow cake coloring in; remove from heat and cool.
