Add 2 tablespoons mustard and 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: cheese bubble loaf
directions: Using white bread dough, let dough rise until doubled.
Divide into 32 equal pieces.
Shape each piece into a ball around a cube of cheese.
Pinch to seal.
Dip balls in melted butter.
Layer, seam side down, in a 9 x 3 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is firm and golden.
Remove from pan; serve warm. Pull apart; do not slice.

title: soupier meat and potato pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Cool a little, then mix in egg and half of the soup, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Press in a casserole dish.
Frost with the potatoes and top with other half of soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening, vanilla and water.
Blend well; beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into 9-inch pie pan.
Pour fruit filling, apple, blueberry or peach into center of batter.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick lemon cookies
directions: Mix until
all	are
softened.	The
dough will be very stiff. Drop
with
a teaspoon on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over all other ingredients.
Chill.
Better the next day.

title: ham cheese rolls
directions: Take
rolls out of the tray and slice them horizontally somewhat
like
you
would split a cake to put filling between the layers.
Spread
the bottom cut portion with a mixture of the butter,
mustard,
Worcestershire
sauce,
poppy seed and grated onion.
Spread ham on the mixture.
Sprinkle completely with grated Parmesan cheese.
Put the second piece back on the rolls. Put
in foil pan.
Brush top with butter, if you wish. Heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: golden pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1/2 cup dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, oil and 1 egg; beat until crumbly.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Press firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In same bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over prepared crust.
Bake for 50 minutes or until set; cool.
Cut into bars.
(Store tightly covered.)

title: pizza burger pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
Heat sour cream, water and shortening until warm.
Add beaten egg; stir in until smooth. Spread batter into 10-inch greased pie pan.
Mix beef, salt, pepper, onion, Italian seasoning and tomato paste; spoon onto batter.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella; add mushrooms.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut into wedges.

title: black joe cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil, coffee and milk. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Mix rice, onion soup, beef consomme, and mushrooms in dish and stir.
Bake at 350 - 400 degrees until dry.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop
popcorn.
Cook together until melted, brown sugar, oleo, light
corn syrup and salt.
After those ingredients are melted, add
teaspoon	oleo
and 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Have popcorn in an extra large bowl (I use my canner).
Pour cooked mixture over popcorn
and stir until evenly coated.
Place in several 2-inch deep
pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15
minutes and breaking apart.
When cool, break apart and store
in airtight
container.
Has
become
a
Christmas tradition with my family.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Fold mayonnaise into yogurt.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Cover.
Chill two hours before serving.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, eggs, parsley and salt.
Mix lightly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown margarine and drain. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: egg and potato casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in the 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until tender. Blend in flour. Stir the sour cream, milk, cheese, parsley, salt, paprika and pepper into the onion mixture. Stir over low heat until the cheese melts. Combine sauce and potatoes.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Place hash browns in bottom of casserole dish and cover with ground beef.
Place a layer of sliced onions on ground beef.
Mix the soup with 2 cups of water and pour over all.
Cover and cook at 325° until thoroughly hot, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Uncover and place slices of Velveeta cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Lay flat and cool. Cook the olive oil and garlic cloves until golden brown. Mix the garlic and oil with the spinach, Ricotta, Parmesan, salt and Mozzarella.
Mix together.
Place the mixture on the noodles and roll each noodle up individually.
Place in a baking pan.
Cover with sauce and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft; beat until fluffy.
Gradually stir in Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla extract; stir until blended.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing top of pie with cherry pie filling.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil; beat well.
Add vanilla, salt, baking powder and flour.
Beat well and spread half of mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with pie filling, then put rest of batter over the berries.
(Batter will be thick so spoon top batter over the whole thing and spread evenly.)
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: beef pot stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until tender.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar. Cream again.
Alternate adding 1 cup flour and 2 eggs until all is added, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Cook in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Melt and bring to boil, brown sugar, dates and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: patio salad
directions: Add frozen peas and salt to water in saucepan.
Cover.
Bring quickly to a full boil.
Then add Minute rice.
Stir with a fork to moisten all rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 13 minutes.
Add mayonnaise, pickle and onion, mixing with fork. Chill.
Before serving, add ham and cheese.
Serve on crisp lettuce with a ring of tomato wedges.
Serves 6.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Mix these ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Allow cake to cool and cut into 4 layers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Separate chicken; place in bottom of ungreased casserole dish. Rinse mixed vegetables with hot water; drain.
Pour these over chicken.
In a small bowl, mix well 1 cup of milk with the cream of chicken soup.
Slowly pour mixture over meat and vegetables. Mix together 1 cup milk, Bisquick and the margarine.
Pour over top of previous layers.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: springtime punch
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the lemon, orange and pineapple juices.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, combine with ginger ale in a large punch bowl.
Yield:
16 to 20 servings (3 quarts).

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Bake cake mix in either 8 or 9 round pan, following directions on box. After cake is cooled, cut each layer in half. (so you have 4 rounded sections). Sprinkle each section with about a teaspoon of liquor. Beat heavy cream add vanilla and sugar to taste. Put bottom layer on plate, put thin layer of cream. Place layer of cake. Then a layer of cherries. Next, layer of cake, and the a layer of cream.
Put top layer of cake and frost whole cake with whipped cream. Decorate with shaved chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: perogies
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Beat with butter and cheese.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In
a
large
mixing
bowl, cream Crisco, margarine and peanut butter;
add
sugars
and
egg,
beating until smooth. Combine dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Chill. Roll
into walnut-size
balls.
Lightly grease a large cookie sheet and place
balls 3 inches apart and flatten with a fork that
has been
dipped
in flour, making crisscross patterns. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except grated cheese. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with the grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all of above ingredients.
Just before serving, add 2 cups of shoestring potatoes.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: key lime cheesecake
directions: In bowl with electric mixer, beat together the cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Now beat in sour cream, flour, eggs (1 at a time), lime juice, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake in center of preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 1 hour.
Let cool on rack, then chill, covered, overnight.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Use crushed chocolate sandwich cookies for the crust, chocolate ice cream for filling and drizzles of chocolate on top for design.

title: "potatoes chantilly"
directions: Put mashed potatoes in a baking dish.
Top with cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in hot oven until cheese is melted and topping is golden brown and bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8. Can freeze. Easy, can do ahead.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Lightly grease baking dish.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread beef in dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour in dish.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes, in a 400° oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: 7 layer vegetable salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order listed in 2-quart bowl.
Spread mayonnaise and sugar and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: best ever blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and mix until smooth. In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this flour mix, alternating with milk to the butter/sugar/eggs.
GENTLY stir in berries.
Line muffin tins with paper and pile high in pan.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden.

title: dill dip with pumpernickel bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream until well blended. Add other ingredients and blend well. Chill before serving. Cut pumpernickel bread into little squares and serve.

title: sally lunn bread(recipe dated 1858)
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in the eggs; whip until fluffy.
Add milk and salt.
Blend in flour and baking powder, then beat mixture 1 full minute.
Pour into well-greased and floured shallow pan; bake in hot oven at 400° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot with plenty of butter, honey, jam, jelly or syrup.

title: aunt mert's cookies
directions: Mix and chill.
Roll into long roll and freeze, or spoon out to cook.
If frozen, just slice off.
Place pecan half on top. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: orange-cranberry relish salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and fruit juice.
Add remaining ingredients and store in the refrigerator.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet.
Remove from heat and drain.
Add other ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or 10 to 12 minutes on high in a microwave.

title: chocolate raspberry truffle cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine 3 (8 ounce) packages of cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla; pour over crust.
Combine remaining cream cheese and melted chocolate, mixing until well blended.
Add preserves; mix well.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of chocolate cream cheese batter over plain cream cheese batter.
Do not swirl. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Melt chocolate pieces and whipping cream over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Spread over cheesecake.
Chill.
Garnish with additional whipped cream, raspberries and mint leaves if desired.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crab creole
directions: Saute celery, green pepper and onion in butter for 5 minutes or until tender.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in tomatoes. Add sugar, salt, pepper, bay leaf and parsley.
Simmer gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add crab meat and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat thoroughly.

title: sweet and sour stir-fry
directions: Bring water in deep skillet to a boil, then add pork and cook until almost done.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Cook until done, then add a mixture of cornstarch, flour and water for thickening.
The flour mixed with the cornstarch will allow you to warm up later.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions in an oblong cake pan. Punch holes in hot cake.
Mix cream of coconut and sweetened milk and pour over cake.
When cool, mix Cool Whip and coconut and put on cake.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain kidney beans and discard liquid.
Combine celery, onion and pickle relish.
Stir in seasonings and mix thoroughly with the beans, being careful not to mash them.
Chill and serve.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 slices bacon.
Pour 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: reindeer fuel homemade irish cream
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.
Store tightly covered in fridge for up to 1 month.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, zucchini, vanilla, and oil.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Pour batter into two 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a wooden toothpick comes out clean when placed in the center of the loaf.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan to finish cooling.
Can be frozen.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind all the vegetables.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well; add salt, sugar and vinegar and boil for 5 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: granny's pea salad
directions: Hard-boil eggs and cook noodles 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, chop tomato, eggs and pickles and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill 3 hours before serving.

title: favorite fruit cobbler
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Drain fruit and arrange in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle fruit with cinnamon and lemon juice. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream the butter with 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Spread this batter over fruit.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup sugar with cornstarch. Sprinkle over batter. Gently pour 1 cup boiling water over entire mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brown onions in pan; add ground beef, salt and pepper until cooked.
Add bread cubes and stir.
Place ground beef mixture inside pumpkin.
Place top back on pumpkin.
Drape 2 slices of bacon over top and hold in place with toothpicks, if necessary.
Cover with aluminum foil and place pumpkin in ovensafe pan.
Cover bottom with water and cook in oven until pumpkin is tender.
Makes a great autumn decorative meal.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
Add gingerale before serving.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, graham crackers and peanut butter. Form into a ball and press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips in double boiler or microwave and spread over mixture.
Cool in fridge until firm.
Cut into squares.
If you like Reese's peanut butter cups, you'll love these!

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Beat all together (except apples, sugar and cinnamon).
Pour 3/4 batter into greased tube pan.
Put 3/4 apples on top of batter and sprinkle 3/4 sugar, cinnamon mixture.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Put remaining apples and sprinkle remaining sugar, cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a round glass or tin cake pan.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add caraway seed.
Using a pastry cutter, two knives or your fingers, cut in the margarine until it is the consistency of fine meal.
Add raisins.
Pour in the buttermilk; mix well.
When the flour is just incorporated, turn the dough out onto a floured board and knead the dough for about 1 to 2 minutes, until it is smooth and no longer sticky.
Form into an 8-inch circle.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place syrup, molasses, salt and vinegar in saucepan and cook to a hard ball stage (265°).
Stir carefully to prevent burning. Remove from heat.
Add butter, stirring only enough to mix.
If desired, add a bit of red and green food color to syrup.
Then pour slowly over popcorn.
Mix well and shape into balls.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Let cool and add strawberries, crushed pineapple and juice and mashed bananas.
Mix together and pour half of mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Let jell.
Spread the sour cream over top and gently pour rest of jello mixture on top.
When set you may decorate with nuts.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Beat buttermilk and pudding until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and oranges.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with fudge stripe cookie crumbs.

title: pina colada punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine pineapple juice, crushed pineapple with juice, cherry 7-Up and maraschino cherries with the juice. When ready to serve, add pina colada sherbet.

title: tomato aspic(serves 12)
directions: Pour into jello mold or square pan.
Put in refrigerator until firmly set.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour; then pour in chocolate syrup.

title: frozen confetti cheesecake
directions: Combine cookies, walnuts and butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; press in place.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and orange juice with mixer in a large bowl until smooth.
Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese.
Stir in candies.
Spoon over crust and freeze until firm.
Thaw for 15 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding with mixer.
Add all Cool Whip and vanilla.
Put frosting in a double boiler and melt on low temperature.
May also be melted in microwave (follow can directions).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer graham crackers and vanilla mixture until gone, ending with graham crackers.
Pour chocolate on top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy; stir in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Pour entire can of peaches and juice into an oiled baking pan. Then add the dry cake mix on top of the peaches.
Place several pieces of margarine on top and sprinkle cinnamon over all.
Place in the oven and bake about 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: apple pineapple cake
directions: Mix
eggs, oil and sugar.
Then add flour, soda, cinnamon
and vanilla.
Add
apples,
pineapple and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for
minutes.
I bake mine in a jelly roll pan. Serve cool with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on packages.
Add condensed milk, Cool Whip and bananas.
Line pan with vanilla wafers and pour mixture over.
Top with wafers and refrigerate.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine can of soup with Miracle Whip, milk and cheese.
Blend well.
Stir in tuna, peas, noodles and onion.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until blended.
Chill.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields 1 quart.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Add grated rind.
Put juice in a measuring cup and fill with water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a bowl, whisk milk and pudding mixes for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened. Stir in sour cream. Fold in whipped topping until well blended. Place half of the vanilla wafers in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish. Top with half of the pudding mixture, half of the bananas, then remaining wafers, bananas and pudding mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Yield: 10 servings.

title: shrimp ala louisiana
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat margarine.
Add the rice, onion and green pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the broth, black pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Lower heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: california tamale casserole
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk and egg in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Brown meat in skillet, stirring to keep crumbly.
Add chili seasoning mix, salt, tomatoes, corn and olives; mix well.
Stir into cornmeal mixture.

title: ritz california vegetables
directions: Put aside 2/3 cup crushed Ritz crackers for top; mix 1 1/3 cups crushed Ritz crackers with 1 stick butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Velveeta cheese with 1/2 stick butter.
Mix cheese mixture with vegetables; put over crackers in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle reserved 2/3 cup cracker crumbs over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be made ahead and reheated in microwave.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: You may need to increase milk if too thick.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Chop onion until translucent.
Add to softened cream cheese. Mix well.
Form into 1 large or 2 medium-sized balls.
Chop nuts. Roll balls until covered in the nuts.
Refrigerate several hours before serving for best flavor.

title: brown sugar loaf cake
directions: Mix all good.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° until done, 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add the milk and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° approximately 10 minutes.

title: peach punch
directions: Dissolve peach Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Mix with lemonade and serve over ice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Mix first 6 ingredients. Top with nuts or coconut.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Can be kept in refrigerator a week.

title: punch
directions: Mix lemon juice and sugar. Add water. Add pineapple, orange juice and cherries (optional). Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: stir-fried peppers with tomatoes
directions: Cook green peppers in olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring often, 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, for 15 minutes or until slightly thickened. Yields 4 servings.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in water, adding salt and oil; cook for 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Pour macaroni into a large salad bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Combine, mixing well.
Cover and chill.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pan and cook 20 minutes.

title: lemon-poppy seed cake(low-fat)
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add vegetable oil and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour into a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: mashed potatoes with carrots and caramelized onions
directions: Saute onion in butter in small skillet over medium-high heat, stirring often until onion is golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Peel potato and carrot.

Cut potato into 8 pieces and carrot into 6. Cook in boiling water until tender 8 to 10 minutes; drain well. Mash potato and carrot together until carrot is in small chunks. Beat in onion, Ricotta cheese and salt.
Cover to keep warm.
Can be reheated in microwave or in double boiler oven on low heat. Serves 2. Increase ingredients as needed.

title: rice with apples
directions: In pot, cover rice with water; bring to boil.
Add milk; boil 10 minutes.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Butter casserole dish.
Mix egg yolk with sugar.
Stir into rice.
Alternate layers starting with rice and then apples into casserole dish.
Top layer must be rice.
Top with bits of butter.
Bake, covered, in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Turn off oven; let stand in oven 1 hour. Serve with a sprinkling of granulated sugar.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions.
Place butter in 9-inch round glass dish.
Roast for 2 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar. Arrange pineapple.
Add cherries.
Add 1/2 prepared cake mix. Microwave on Simmer 7 minutes.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend with mixer powdered sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese.
Slowly add sweet milk.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell (10-inch size is best).
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate. Keeps well for several days.

title: italian hero loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix in enough reserved flour to make soft dough.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Add seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil while stirring.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: egg in a cup
directions: Butter 1 slice of bread for each person.
Place the buttered side of the bread down in each muffin cup.
Put a bacon slice on top of the bread and crack an egg into the center of the bread cup.
Bake them in the oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove the muffin pan from the oven using hot pads.
(Make sure there is an adult there to supervise.)

title: yummy banana pancakes
directions: Beat 3 eggs until light.
Add 3 cups buttermilk, 3 tablespoons butter and ripe banana.
Combine the dry ingredients with the liquid ingredients.
Cook on medium hot griddle.
Makes 24 medium pancakes.
Freeze extras for easy, healthy breakfast, lunch or snacks.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Dredge chops with flour and brown in hot fat.
Set aside.
Put sliced potatoes in buttered casserole with onion, salt and pepper. Stir soup well and pour over potatoes.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are well done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first six ingredients and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oats and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: grandmother's rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, beating well. Add butter.
Combine rice and egg mixture.
Add vanilla and spices.
Add milk, beating well.

title: toast spread
directions: *For large quantity of the spread.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Use 3 egg whites for meringue.
Use baked crust or crumbs.
If crumbs, sprinkle on top.

title: glazed ham balls
directions: Mix together lightly but well the ground meats, graham cracker crumbs, milk and eggs.
Shape into balls about walnut size or whatever you prefer.
Place in single layer in two 9 x 13-inch pans or sizes to suit your family.
Top with glaze and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes about 80 meat balls.

title: delphia runyon's 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and 7-Up.
Let set until partially jelled. Add fruits.
Chill until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add and mix sugar, syrup, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: battleship
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into a large baking pan with lid. Crumble raw hamburger on top of potatoes; dice onion and spread over hamburger.
Put pork and beans on then spread tomato soup on top.
Cook with lid on for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, cocoa and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on foil or wax paper.
Makes 50 to 55 cookies.

title: russian tea cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix and divide dough in half.
Press 1/2 of the dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Press other half of dough onto wax paper the size of pan, then turn onto pie filling in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until brown. While hot, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, salt, syrup, syrup and vanilla.
Stir in flour or cornstarch.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover top with pecan halves. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Center will still be soft, however, do not overbake as pie will set as it cools.

title: breakfast bundt cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding, oil, water, eggs, vanilla and butter flavoring; beat for 6 minutes.
In separate bowl mix together sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Pour batter and nuts alternately into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Invert onto cake plate.
Poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Prepare Glaze; spoon over hot cake.

title: basic pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
With a fork, stir in enough cold water (1 tablespoon at a time) to moisten dry ingredients. Shape dough into a ball.
Dough is ready to roll out.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch shell.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with the flour.
Add cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Add jam last. Bake in two or three layers in moderate oven until brown.

title: aunt jill's chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and 2 cups cold water.
Blend until mixed well.
Put in 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: emily's cheesy fish soup
directions: Cut fish into large (3 inch) cubes.
In 3-quart pot, melt butter and saute onion, green pepper and celery until tender-crisp.
Blend in flour, salt, marjoram and paprika. Gradually add bouillon and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add fish and cheese and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up.
Cook until creamy.
Add food coloring; let cool.
Mix in strawberries; cook pie crust sprinkled with sugar.
Pour mixture into crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen berries; stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple and juice (also bananas).
Pour 1/2 jello mixture in a large glass pan and chill until set.
Then spread with sour cream and cover with remaining jello and chill.

title: chocolate almond tea bread
directions: Blend together all ingredients until smooth.
Place in well-buttered bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before unmolding.
Cool before cutting.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: *If using Minute rice, go by directions on back of label.

title: virginia's congealed lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cream cheese in one cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup syrup from pears or syrup-water combination.
Let partly set.
Add pears and nuts.

title: lemon maple punch
directions: Bring syrup and lemon juice almost to a boil.
Add whiskey. Serve with nutmeg sprinkled on top and float a lemon slice. Makes 18 cups.

title: louise's banana nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar, butter, and oil. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Alternate flour and mashed bananas.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done, when tested with a toothpick.
Top with icing when cooled.

title: honey roasted peanut cookies
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar until well blended.
Add peanut butter, egg, vanilla and honey; mix well.

title: florentine beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano in olive oil over medium heat.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in flour.
Add beef broth and cook until thickened.
Stir in sour cream.
Add drained spinach.
Put meat mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cut cheese into strips and place on top of meat, criss-crossing the strips to decorate.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until casserole is heated through and cheese is melted.

title: the bachelor's survival supper
directions: Make according to manufacturer's directions.

title: homemade divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until mixture dropped in cold water turns brittle (no longer, watch close, test often).
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten whites of egg; add nuts and flavoring. Beat until mixture is creamy.
Pour on buttered platter.

title: lola hexom's asparagus corned beef casserole
directions: Cook Creamettes in unsalted water; drain.
Add mushroom soup and heat until blended.
Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese and let melt.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Use a greased casserole.
Pour sauce over all and stir lightly.
Put potato chips on top.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 15.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir at least half of hot mixture gradually into egg yolks.
Blend into hot mixture.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, lemon peel and lemon juice. Pour into pie shell.
Spoon meringue over hot filling.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and mix taco seasoning as directed.
Spread cream cheese in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Drain excess liquid off hamburger and spread over cream cheese.
Spoon salsa over meat.
Put sour cream over hamburger and salsa.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomato, sliced ripe olives and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: heavenly corn rolls
directions: Make a mush by cooking cornmeal in 2 c. milk; stir until milk is gone and meal is thick (burns easily), set aside to cool.
Add scalded milk and water to a large bowl; add yeast and sugar.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Mix other ingredients, adding the mush with the beaten eggs.
This is a fairly stick dough.
Use plenty of flour on a cloth to knead.
Let rise.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Tie strips into knots and dip in melted butter.
Let them rise.
Bake at 350 degrees.
Keeps well and reheats well.

title: seafood in rice cooker
directions: Spray rice cooker with Pam.
Put all ingredients in and stir; cook as usual for rice cooker.

title: ann's marinara sauce
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine onion, garlic and parsley; saute in olive oil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add tomatoes, paste, water, sugar, basil leaves, salt and pepper. Bring to a slow boil, then lower heat and simmer for 1/2 hour over low heat.
Makes 3 quarts.
May be frozen in plastic containers.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Beat egg whites with sugar and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Shape to fit a greased 10-inch pie plate and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool. When cooled, cover bottom of crust with a layer of pineapple, then a layer of sliced bananas.
Next, cover with chopped nuts.
Top nuts with whipped cream.
Sprinkle pie with toasted coconut.
Chill 6 hours before serving.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix all in one large pan.
Melt oleo.
Add sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add drained pineapple and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: pan handy pudding cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Make a hole in the center.
Add the vinegar, vanilla, oil and water.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 12.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Melt caramels in water in saucepan over low heat.
Toss bread with margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
In 8-inch square pan, layer 1/2 apples, 1/2 nuts, 1/2 caramel sauce and 1/2 bread cubes. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Measure into bowl the flour, sugar, shortening, crushed graham crackers, salt and 3/4
cup
milk.
Beat for 2 minutes. Stir in baking powder; add
eggs,
cup
milk and vanilla. Mix for 2 more minutes.
Grease
and flour pans.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with Lemon Icing.
Decorate with 1 teaspoon graham cracker crumbs.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for a couple of hours before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry hamburger with onion and seasonings until hamburger is brown and onion cooked.
Add tomato paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Beat egg yolk and milk together in saucepan; add sugar, butter and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cool until thick enough to spread, beating occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and soda.
Add milk and cracklings. Grease baking sheet.
Spoon mixture in.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes enough sauce to baste 3 pounds of ribs.

title: skillet herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet over medium high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides; push chicken to one side.
Stir in soup and water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve over hot rice. Garnish with fresh thyme, if desired.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender or mixer.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes a large pie.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar, milk and dates until soft ball forms in cold water. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Make cake and cool slightly.
With a toothpick, poke holes in top.
Mix together Eagle Brand and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake.
Mix coconut and Cool Whip together; spread on top of cake. Save a little coconut to sprinkle on top.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast in lukewarm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar, and flour; make stiff dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out.
Dip in melted butter.
Put in pan; let rise again.
Bake in oven at 400° to golden brown.

title: bonnie's walnut rum raisin cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine raisins and rum.
Set aside.
Combine graham crackers, walnuts, sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Press firmly on the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan or a 9-inch baking pan.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots in lengthwise pieces; pack in canning jars.
Add slice of green and red bell peppers, 2 cloves of garlic per pint and 1 red hot pepper pod per pint.
Boil 2 cups white vinegar and 1 1/2 tablespoons salt and pour over carrots.
Ready in 3 to 4 weeks.

title: kansas city baked beans
directions: Layer half of beans in casserole dish, then pepper, onion and tomato mixture.
Cover with bacon and layer remaining beans on top. Cover with small bottle of catsup.
Cook 1 hour, covered, at 350° and 1 hour, uncovered.

title: corn dog days
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and mustard.
Stir in milk, egg and oil.
Lightly roll each frank in additional flour, insert wooden skewer.
Dip into cornmeal batter, coating evenly.
Drain off excess.
Fry in hot deep fat until golden brown.
Drain and serve with catsup.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat some oil in pan, add garlic and brown chicken pieces. Add remaining ingredients to pan and cook until thicken is tender. If needed, add more water to sauce.
Serve chicken and sauce over wide noodles.

title: fudge cake
directions: I mix the dry ingredients and the liquid ingredients separately and then put them together.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 round pans or 1 long pan or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked steak
directions: Brown steak in skillet	(does
not
have
to
be done). Salt and pepper the steak.
Put	steak in a Pyrex dish.	Drain mixed vegetables.
Pour
over steak.
Sprinkle vegetables with Worcestershire sauce.
Pour 1 cup
tomato soup and 1 cup water over mixture.
Bake 25 to
minutes until tender.
Take out of oven; sprinkle top	with
crushed
potato
chips or cereal. Brown in oven.

title: squash delight
directions: Layer squash in baking dish with tomatoes over squash. Top with sliced onions. Sprinkle salt and pepper. Bake, covered tightly, for about 1 hour in 350° oven. No calories!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and break into small flowerettes.
Combine ingredients in bowl and mix thoroughly.

title: sky-high biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the flours, baking powder, sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Cut in butter until
mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add egg and milk, stirring quickly and briefly.

title: hot chicken for sandwiches
directions: Cook chicken until tender, remove from bone and chop or tear in small pieces.
Add eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix with broth until very moist.
Bake at 300° stirring occasionally until it is cooked down, but still moist.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter.
Add melted chocolate and all other ingredients. Spread on greased cookie pan; bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into squares while hot.
Yields about 20.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Stir in pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Pour into oblong casserole and let congeal.
Blend and mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla and spread over congealed mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cover and chill. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: no sugar fruit cake
directions: Mix this with the first mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 big loaf.
Nuts can be added, if desired.

title: oven baked split pea soup
directions: Rinse peas under cold water.
In a 4 1/2 quart Dutch oven combine peas, water, carrot, celery, onion, thyme, celery seed, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bake, covered, in 350° 2 hours.
Add sausage; bake 30 minutes more or until peas are tender and sausage is heated through.
Remove bay leaf.
Ladle into bowls.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain corn, Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Mix all together. Mix cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter together and line pie plate.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Whip one package Dream Whip and mix with the cheese mixture.
Place in shell and cover with pie filling.
It can be cherry, pineapple or blueberry.
Freeze before serving.

title: chili(yields 8 quarts; freezes well)
directions: Wash beans; cover with water by 2-inches.
Simmer until tender. Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Cook onions in salad oil slowly until tender, stirring frequently.
Add garlic and parsley.
In large skillet, saute beef and pork 15 minutes.
Remove any grease that cooks out of the meat.
Add this mixture to beans and season with salt, pepper and cumin.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove cover and cook 30 minutes.
Skim any fat off top before serving. Flavor is better the second day.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Put salmon with liquid into a bowl.
Remove bones and flake salmon.
Combine milk and bread crumbs.
Add to salmon and mix gently with fork.
Add egg, salt, poultry seasoning, celery, green pepper, lemon juice and onion.
Mix.
Turn mixture into well-greased 1-quart ring mold.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in a pot with water to cover and 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Bring to boiling over medium heat.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain eggs.
Cover with cold water. When cool, drain and peel.
Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks to small bowl.
Mash with fork.
Mix in 1 tablespoon vinegar, one third cup half and half, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Heat oil in a 10 to 12-inch skillet.
Beat eggs in bowl until foamy.
Stir in bean sprouts, bamboo shoots, chicken, 2 tablespoons scallions and 1 tablespoon soy sauce for each pancake. Pour 1/4 cup of mixture into skillet.
As egg mixture sets around the edge, push it up over the meat with a spatula to form a patty. When patties are set, turn them to brown on other side.
Put onto plates.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Combine dip and seasoning mix, spread thin layer on a platter (10-inch or larger).
Then spread avocado dip (optional, room temperature to spread).
Then mix sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over dip. Then spread mixed shredded cheese over dip.
Top with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Serve with chips.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add egg; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in peanut butter morsels.
Pour into foil lined 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: apple-nut squares
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add together and mix thoroughly.
Add apples and nuts. Spread into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: candy cookies
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Mix Eagle Brand milk in.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator, the mix in Cool Whip the next day.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix together and beat well on medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 35 minutes.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with ice pick or fork.
Drizzle icing over cake.

title: baked lima beans
directions: In saucepan, place beans in water to cover.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Slice 1 onion into thin slices.
Stud the other onion with cloves.
In small bowl, mix mustard, ginger, brown sugar, sliced onion and ketchup with 1 cup of reserved liquid. Arrange 4 slices of raw bacon in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add beans and pour on the liquid mixture.
Place whole onion in the center, pushing it down.
Arrange remaining bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with lid or foil.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Bring meat and water to a boil in a large, heavy saucepan, then reduce heat and simmer covered until meat is very tender, about an hour.
Remove meat, set aside.
Add the vegetables, bouillon and seasonings.
Bring to a boil over high heat, cover and reduce heat to simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk in a large mixing bowl; add pudding mix and mix on low until it thickens.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping and make sure it's well blended.

Place a layer of vanilla wafers on the bottom of a large, deep dish, then a layer of banana slices, then cover with half of the pudding mixture. Repeat with more cookies and bananas, then remaining pudding. Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: two hour buns
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients until foamy.
Add the shortening, salt and flour.
Knead just enough to mix well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Make into buns.
Let rise again; bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400° to 450°.

title: red vegetable salad
directions: Cut potatoes in thin slices and the beets fine.
Slice the cabbage as thin as possible.
Mix all the ingredients.
Let stand in a cold place 1 hour, then serve.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: paska
directions: Dissolve sugar in lukewarm water and add yeast; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add lukewarm milk and 4 1/2 cups flour.
Mix until smooth; let rise until bubbly.
Add eggs, raisins, sugar, butter and salt; mix thoroughly.
Add enough flour to make a dough that does not stick to your hand.
Knead until shining.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Divide and round dough into 3 balls, 1 for each loaf (medium-sized).
Place in greased round pans to double in size.
Brush with a beaten egg, mixed with 2 tablespoons water.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Combine all except potatoes in saucepan.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in hash browns that have been thawed at room temperature.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil until the last 15 minutes.

title: mom's spiced cookies
directions: Mix softened butter, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla and molasses. Gradually add all other ingredients until dough is formed.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap.
Chill for 1 hour.
Divide dough in half. Roll to 1/8-inch thickness and shape with cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: kelly's karamels
directions: Melt the caramel candies with the water in microwave.
Mix the flour, oatmeal, sugar, margarine, baking soda and salt.
Save 1 cup.
Place oatmeal mixture (less 1 cup) in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Add the caramel mixture.
Put the 1 cup of oatmeal mixture on top.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate until gelatin sets.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Measure flour, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add shortening, baking powder and soda.
Combine egg and buttermilk. Stir into mixture and beat smooth.
Oil and flour a long pan or 2 cake pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Check with toothpick to see if done.
Use as a dessert with ice cream or serve as a cornbread.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Cream cheese, butter, baking powder and salt.
Add flour.
Mix well with hands.
Pinch off and mash out flat.
Put olive in the middle and dough around it well.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 balls.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Heat syrup and add sugar. Bring to a rolling boil and add peanut butter. Mix until smooth. Pour over rice Krispies, stirring well. Put in a 9 x 13 Pan.

title: lacy swedish almond wafers
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and cook until smooth. Add almonds.
Drop by level tablespoon onto lightly greased and floured cookie sheet approximately 4 inches apart.
Because cookies will spread, place only 4 to 6 cookies on cookie sheet at one time.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool slightly.
Carefully lift each cookie, using a wide spatula, and place on dowel or rolling pin to cool into curved shape.
If cookie hardens before removing from pan, return pan to oven for a few seconds to soften cookies.
Remember to grease and flour cookie sheet with each batch.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: 1-2-3 cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter, sugar and water.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in Bisquick.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Beat condensed milk with lemon juice in bowl until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese until fluffy.
Serve with your favorite fruit.

title: peach pie
directions: Peel and stir.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Put a tablespoon Minute tapioca in bottom of pie shell. Add the peaches. After first layer of peaches, put in another tablespoon Minute tapioca. Add more peaches until you have a filled pie shell.
Pour the mixture over the peaches and bake 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
As broccoli cooks, melt butter in large pot.
Saute onion and garlic until tender; sprinkle flour over onion and garlic.
Stir until blended.
Add stock and continue stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add cheese and broccoli; beat until cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix.
Refrigerate until cold. Before serving, add 1/2 gallon pineapple sherbet and 1 large ginger ale.

title: sweet williams homemade lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons.
Add sugar and water.
Stir until sugar has dissolved.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well.
The longer it sets the better it tastes.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with fresh vegetables or chips.
Double batch makes enough to serve 50 people.

title: oriental salad
directions: Cut everything in large bowl.
Rice sticks are to be deep fried and drained on paper towels.

title: carrot-apple salad
directions: Mix the first 4
ingredients in large serving dish. Add enough mayonnaise to lightly coat the ingredients.

title: crab cakes(smith island, maryland)
directions: Mix the ingredients with a spoon.
Form the cakes with an ice cream dipper.
Cook in an inch of hot oil until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: kraut for hot dogs
directions: Mix ahead of time and let stand.

title: easy crab appetizers
directions: Place block of cream cheese in the middle of serving plate. Place crab meat on top of cream cheese.
Pour cocktail sauce on top of crab meat.

title: dream delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 5 minutes or for firmer crust bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot fudge cake with icing
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Bring butter, cocoa and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add sugar and flour mixture.
Mix on slow speed until well blended.
Add egg, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes in a baking pan.

title: paul's pineapple pudding
directions: Drain sliced pineapple; reserve juice and use for another purpose such as adding to orange juice for breakfast.
Place slices in the bottom of a baking dish; they fit in a 10-inch ceramic pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: trish-a-bobs
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch pieces.
Whisk together oil, lemon juice, water, mustard, honey, oregano and pepper in large bowl.
Add chicken, bell pepper and mushrooms, stirring to coat.
Alternately thread ingredients on each of four 12-inch skewers.
Place Trish-A-Bobs on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 3 to 4 inches from heat.
Broil 9 minutes, turning occasionally.
Season with salt if desired.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add other ingredients, mixing well. Chill and serve with sliced fresh apples.

title: peanut's fruit cobbler
directions: Cover fruit with water and boil 10 minutes.
Melt butter rin baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour flour mixture into baking pan.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake until brown at 375°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring all to a boil; simmer for 55 minutes.
Stir very often. Remove from heat and stir in 3/4 can of Carnation evaporated milk. Beat 2 eggs in a blender and fold in.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Stir very often so it doesn't burn.

title: ready the night before hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with heavy foil several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: family favorite banana pudding
directions: Use a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine dry ingredients (except 1/4 cup sugar) in saucepan.
Blend slightly beaten yolks and milk well.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened over medium heat.
Don't leave the pot.
Stir gently.
Reduce heat to very low.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Add vanilla.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together with crackers.
Put on baking sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and combine soup and broccoli in a baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Divide the biscuits in halves by separating the layers.
Place each biscuit portion in a greased muffin pan (I use the mini pan), pressing the dough to cover bottom and sides of the pan.
Spoon the meat mixture into the biscuit lined muffin pans.
Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
(Any leftover meat makes great tacos.)
Makes 3 servings.

title: grilled chicken and potato dinner
directions: Prepare grill.
Place potatoes in a steamer basket over boiling water.
Cover pan and steam 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain, transfer to a bowl and toss with oil.
When cool enough to handle, thread potatoes onto skewers.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, milk, garlic salt, pepper, onion, rice and meat. Mix thoroughly. Press half mixture into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Place cheese on meat. Spread remaining meat mixture over cheese, being certain cheese is completely covered. Spoon ketchup over loaf. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until meat is done. Remove from oven and let cool for 5 minutes before slicing and serving.

title: frankfurter scallop
directions: In nonstick 9-inch square baking pan, layer half the potatoes, the onion, the frankfurters and remaining potatoes.
In small bowl, combine milk, flour, salt, paprika and mustard.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 servings, about 275 calories each.

title: twice baked cottage-style potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cook potatoes until done.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Set aside.
Mash pulp.
Combine cottage cheese and milk in container of an electric blender and process until smooth.
Add cottage cheese mixture, green onions, salt and pepper to potato pulp; stir well.
Stuff shells with potato mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until heated.
Garnish if desired.
Contains 1.1 grams fat and 3 milligrams cholesterol.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients well and set aside.
Take clean, wet dish cloth and wipe off mushrooms.
Pop out stems and stuff with sausage mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: forbus fajitas
directions: Cut peppers and onions into small strips.
Place in large skillet with margarine and wine.
Cook on medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until wine is almost absorbed and peppers and onions are done.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Make sure that all ingredients are diced the same size as the peas.

title: chase and wyatt's favorite yum-yum
directions: Mix melted butter and 1 1/2 sleeves Ritz crackers. Layer to form a crust to cover bottom of large square pan. Mix ice cream, pudding mix and milk with mixer on low speed. Pour over cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: big mama's chicken pie
directions: Cut up cooked chicken; mix with broth and cream of chicken soup.
Place in baking dish and cover chicken mixture with chopped hard-cooked eggs.
(Use salt, pepper, seasoned salt or whatever seasonings you prefer.)
Mix together milk, flour and margarine; pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until brown (approximately 45 minutes).

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese with sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flavorings.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and morsels.

title: broiled porgies(psaritsipoures)
directions: Wash the fish in cold water
and pat dry.
Rub fish all over with some olive oil.
Broil both sides of fish until they are done.
(This may take 15 minutes or more, depending on the size of the fish.) Beat the lemon juice and olive oil together with a fork and pour over the
fish
when
it comes out of the broiler.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Use regular size loaf pan, greased and floured.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Easy and delicious!

title: crispy treats
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan on low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spread Rice Krispies in a buttered plate.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap; pound to 1/2-inch thickness.
Remove wrap.
Coat chicken with 1/2 cup flour.
Mix eggs and 3 tablespoons milk; dip chicken in the mixture to coat.
Next, coat with bread crumbs.
In a skillet, fry the chicken in hot oil about 5 minutes per side, or until golden brown.
Remove to platter; cover and keep warm.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice unpeeled cucumbers.
Add salt.
Mix well.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain liquid from mixture.
Do not rinse.
Mix in sugar, onions and vinegar.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread large can crushed pineapple in bottom of pan.
Put cherry filling on top of pineapple.
Pour yellow cake mix over pineapple and cherry.
Slice 1/2 pound butter thin and place over cake mix.
Spread coconut over butter and top with broken pecans. Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: rice with mushrooms
directions: Put everything in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and stir.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: lutefisk pudding
directions: Clean and wash fish well.
Put fish, skin side up, in colander.
Place the colander in salted water, 1/3 cup salt to 2 quarts water, in large kettle.
If fish is to be kept firm, simmer until tender, usually about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove colander and drain fish over the sink.
Place fish on a large platter and serve with melted butter.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat together condensed milk, lemon juice and pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crust or baked pie shell.
Chill.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Add grated rind and juice to the egg yolks which have been beaten until thick and lemon colored. Add mixture of sugar and flour slowly. Beat well. Add milk slowly. Beat egg whites until stiff enough to hold their shape. Fold into mixture. Pour into shallow 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Set in pan of cold water. Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven. Will have spongy top with lemon custard underneath. Serves 6.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding in large bowl.
Blend in eggs, oil, 4 ounces liquor Galliano, vodka and orange juice.
Mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cut chicken in strips.
Put oil in skillet.
Add beans and ginger.
Cook three minutes.
Add chicken and carrots.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Add soup with 1/4 cup water, sherry and soy sauce.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.
Serve over rice.

title: butter chicken
directions: Grate the 4 tomatoes and strain out the juice.
Fry onion in butter until pale in color.
Add ginger, garlic, and saute 1 minute.
Add tomato juice and all remaining ingredients.
Cook gravy over low heat for 10 minutes.
Then add the chicken pieces. Simmer for 3-4 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine meats and salt; blend lightly.
Add bread crumbs that have been soaked in water and drained.
Stir in allspice, nutmeg and onion.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in butter or margarine.
Add water to cover.
Cover pan and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add bouillon; stir until dissolved.
Thicken sauce.
Makes 48 balls or 12 portions.

title: cinnamon rolls(sticky biscuits)
directions: Flatten biscuits; dip into melted butter.
Drain off excess butter; now dip buttered biscuit into the bowl of cinnamon and sugar.
Flip biscuit until covered.
Place 4 to 6 mini marshmallows into center; pinch biscuit over marshmallows.
Repeat for all.
Cook 11 to 13 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Let cool. If using spears, cut into chunks. Crush crackers. Melt 1 stick of butter and pour over crackers. Set aside. Melt 2 sticks of butter and cheese together. Put 1/2 crackers and butter mixture in baking dish. Put broccoli in next followed by the cheese and butter mixture. Top with remaining crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: springerle cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light, gradually add sugar and continue beating at a high speed for 15 to 20 minutes until batter is thick and lemon colored.
Add anise.
Sift flour and soda and blend with egg mixture at a low speed.
Cover bowl with wax paper or foil and let stand 15 minutes (so it is easier to work with).
Divide into 3 parts.
On lightly floured surface roll dough to 8-inch square, 1/4 inch thick.
Let rest 1 minute.
Flour mold and press design, cut and place on lightly floured surface.
Cover with a towel all night.
Grease a cookie sheet well.
Brush off excess flour from the cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.
Yield 6 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Then, add beaten eggs into the oil and add to the first mixture.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bread roll
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients together and add to pumpkin mixture.
Spread on greased and floured wax paper in oblong pan; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto confectioners sugar-covered cloth; peel off wax paper.
Roll up (very easy) and let cool.
Add filling and re-roll.

title: peasant's caviar
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut eggplants in half lengthwise.
Make deep slits in the flesh (do not pierce the skin) and insert 2 cloves garlic in each half.
Place eggplants in shallow roasting pan, skin side down, and sprinkle tops with salt.
Cover with foil and bake for one hour or until eggplants and garlic are tender. Cool.
With a spoon, scoop eggplants and garlic out of skin into bowl.
Mash well with fork.
Stir in lemon juice, oil, pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Gently fold in remaining ingredients except endive.
Refrigerate, covered to chill.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Mix and roll out 1/2 to 1-inch thick. Cut biscuits with a glass.
Baste with melted butter before and after baking.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix Ranch dressing and cream cheese.
Place crescent rolls on cookie sheet; bake as package directs.
When cool, spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Place veggies on top.
Slice in small pieces and chill for an hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes; drain.
Fry bacon and add onion and cook until onion is soft.
Add bacon and onion to potatoes and set aside. Put remaining ingredients into a saucepan and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add potato mixture.
Stir and cook over low heat.
Do not boil.

title: butch's pan fry
directions: In medium skillet with oil, cut sausage into thin round pieces. Fry sausage until done, then remove and drain.
Add potatoes and onions.
Cook on medium high heat with enough water to make steam. Keep adding water.
Cover until water is gone and potatoes and onions are done.
Add sausage to pan.
Simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Enjoy!

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix milk and eggs together.
Dip eggplant, peeled and sliced, into egg mixture; shake in Shake 'n Bake until coated.
Fry in oil until tender.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, egg and molasses, blending well. Mix together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: cheese, broccoli, rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, not brown.
Cook rice for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Boil broccoli until tender and drain.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Let sit 24 hours; drain.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first six ingredients.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 375° for 10-12 minute.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread in 13 x 9 inch pan.
In a medium bowl mix sugar and eggs.
Add cinnamon or vanilla to taste and raisins if preferred.
Pour over bread, mix well.
Add milk until all the bread is very moist.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Bread will pull away from side of pan when done.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crush crackers.
Chop nuts.
Cut cherries and grind coconut. Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Line graham cracker box with aluminum foil and pack cake in it.
Keep in refrigerator for a month or longer.

title: gertrude armstrong's oklahoma cake
directions: Add first 4 ingredients together.
Mix well and let come to a boil. Set aside to cool.
Mix flour, sugar (granulated), soda, buttermilk and vanilla to taste. Add boiled mixture and stir real well.
Pour in an 8 x 13-inch pan. Cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Punch holes in cake.
Make frosting with the oleo, cocoa, powdered sugar, vanilla and enough milk to be creamy.
Heat and pour over cake while hot. Do not boil.

title: apple dip
directions: Crush enough peanuts to cover 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then sprinkle brown sugar over nuts.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over nuts.
Slice apples and stand them up in the pan.

title: crunchy brownie ice cream dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix and stir (crumble).
Place in oven for 20 minutes, turning occasionally as baking.
Remove and cool completely.
Save 1 1/2 cups for topping. Mix the rest into 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream.
Put on topping and drizzle chocolate syrup over crumb topping.
Refreeze and serve.

title: special k treats
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Special K.
Drop on wax paper and cool.

title: southwestern rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Frozen bread loaves, let thaw and rise at least 8°.
Roll out like a round pizza (very thin).
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and chipped pepperoni slices.
If you like hot also include hot pepper seed or fresh hot peppers.
My favorites!
Roll very tight; long ways and place on greased cookie sheet diagonally.
Cut slits on top and rub top with egg to glaze and sprinkle sesame seed on top.
Follow baking directions on bread package.
After cool, slice.
Enjoy!

title: tea cookies
directions: In medium bowl beat the butter, sugar and vanilla extract until smooth and creamy.
Mix in flour and salt until well combined.
Add the nuts, mixing well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or until dough is stiff enough to shape into marble size balls.
Place cookies on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll into powdered sugar.
Let cool.
Roll in sugar again.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Trim fat off chops and brown in oil in skillet.
Remove and set aside.
Add to skillet green pepper, celery and onion.
Saute lightly and drain off fat.

title: stuffed white scalloped squash
directions: Slice tops off squash.
Scoop out seed.
Mix stuffing mix with chicken broth as liquid according to package directions, adding onion and celery.
Fill squash with mix, rounding up well.
Bake at 350° until squash is tender.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir well.
Pour into 8-inch square pan and freeze for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain and cook.
Mix beaten eggs, mayonnaise, mushroom soup and onions.
Layer broccoli, cheese and mixture.
Sprinkle potato chips or crushed cracker crumbs on top. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pennsylvania dutch meat and cabbage
directions: Mix together lightly and thoroughly the beef, salt, pepper and egg; mix in rice.
Cook cabbage leaves in salted water just until tender; drain.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add the onion and cook until tender.

Blend in a mixture of the soup and water; add celery, parsley, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper; simmer 10 minutes. Place 1/4 cup of the meat mixture in the center of each leaf and roll up tucking ends in toward center.
Use wooden picks to hold. Place rolls in a large, heavy skillet.
Pour sauce over rolls, cover tightly and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain yams; mash thoroughly.
Mix the ingredients and spread in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix and set aside to cool the water and Bran Buds.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs and buttermilk.
Add the Bran Buds.
Sift the flour, soda and salt together.
Add to the shortening mixture.
Add the All-Bran and stir.
Add the nuts, raisins or dates as desired.
Can be stored in glass jars in refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.
Recipe can be cut in half.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, then lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours before eating.

title: dalmatian sea beast fest
directions: Place garlic and parsley in oil and simmer in a skillet over medium heat until garlic becomes yellow.
Add shrimp.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add cooking wine and simmer over a medium heat 10 more minutes, stirring frequently.
At this point, if the sauce is not thick enough, 1 to 3 tablespoons of plain bread crumbs may be added as a thickener.
Serves 4.
Best served with peeled, boiled potatoes.

title: savory chicken bites
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Stir in chicken, celery and pimento; set aside.

title: frozen cranberry cheese salad
directions: Cream the cheese and mix well with mayonnaise.
Whip cream and add.
Fold in sliced olives, crushed pineapple and cranberry sauce cubes.
Pack in refrigerator tray and freeze for 3 to 4 hours. Slice and serve on lettuce.

title: pot roast
directions: For each cup of broth, mix 1/4 cup cold water and 2 tablespoons flour. Mix until smooth and add to boiling broth, stirring constantly. Cook 1 minute or until thickened.

title: betty's fudge
directions: Cook on medium-high heat the first 4 ingredients until mixture starts boiling, then turn to low heat and cook approximately 7 minutes.
Pour in mixing bowl and add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat with electric mixer until mixture begins to get firm.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let set several hours so jello blends well.

title: dirt pie
directions: Combine pudding and milk in a medium bowl and beat until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes then fold in Cool Whip.
Stir 1 cup of the cookies into the pudding.
Spoon into the pie crust. Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze about 4 hours.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all, except corn muffin mix, then add mix.
Turn into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut in small wedges.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: Brown the chicken in the vegetable oil in a frying pan.
Add the onion and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in the soup, water and soy sauce (I've never tried it with soy sauce but the recipe calls for it).
Heat to boiling.
Reduce the heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. Serve over rice.
(I use Minute rice, since it can be soaking while you're cooking the chicken mixture.)

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buttermilk.
Add enough buttermilk to form a pouring consistency, like cake batter.
Pour into a hot, greased iron skillet or baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken, salt and black pepper in a large pot.
Boil over medium heat until tender.
Remove chicken from stock. Combine flour, shortening and water in a mixing pan.
Mix well to form soft dough.
Roll out paper thin.
Cut in small strips.
Drop in boiling broth.
Stir lightly.
Cook dumplings for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and add chicken.
Serve hot.

title: banana split cake
