directions: Combine cracker crumbs and one stick butter.
Pack into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks butter and powdered sugar together for no less than 15 minutes.
Spread this over the unbaked crumb crust.
Add the sliced bananas and pineapple.
Add layer of whipped topping.
Top with chopped cherries and pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Mix popped corn and nuts in a large mixing bowl.
Combine sugar, margarine and corn syrup in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil (stirring) 10 to 15 minutes, or until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and nuts, mixing to coat well.
Spread to dry on ungreased cookie sheet.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: easy vanilla mousse
directions: Pour water and gelatin into blender.
Process on high for 30 seconds.
Add sugar.
Process 5 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients except fruit.
Process 1 minute or until mixture is smooth.
Pour into dessert dishes and chill 1 hour.
Serve, topped with fresh berries.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks and shortening.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites last.
Fold into batter.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: pasta alla puttanesca
directions: Soak sun-dried tomatoes in hot water until softened, then cut into bite size pieces.
Saute garlic in the olive oil in a large saucepan.
Add the crushed tomatoes and all other ingredients, except the parsley.
Simmer about 15 minutes to blend the flavors. Add the parsley; simmer a few minutes longer.
Serve over fresh cooked pasta (penne and rotelli are recommended).

title: honey-oat bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add sour or buttermilk and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Combine eggs, oil and honey and add to first mixture.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda and add all at once to egg mixture.
Stir until well-moistened. Fill muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Grate cheese.
Chop celery.
Smash Ritz crackers.
Beat eggs.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast beef supreme
directions: Put roast in heavy aluminum foil. Cover with onions, pepper, celery and orange juice.
Sprinkle garlic and wine over meat. Wrap foil tight.
Roast at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: jerry's bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Drain and top with 6 cups of water.
Simmer until done.
Add 1 can of tomato soup.
Also add 1 pound cooked ground beef.
Simmer a few more minutes.
Do not add salt of any kind until the last 5 minutes as this toughens the beans and the cooking time will take twice as long.

title: cheez thing
directions: Punch holes in a paper bag.
Put tomatoes in there then put 1 banana in there.
Set it all in the cabinet.
Leave it for a few days.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar, cornstarch, cocoa, melted oleo and vanilla flavoring.
Beat and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This makes a thick pie.

title: edna's pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Season pork chops and brown on both sides.
Put in a baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: light orange sauce for vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients in small saucepan, stirring often.
Cook over low heat until heated through.

title: cheese-broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth for 15 minutes.
Saute in butter until tender.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add all the milk and cook until thickened.
Add to broccoli and broth. Add cheese and stir until it melts.
Turn stove to simmer and cook for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Season to taste.
Makes about 3-quarts.

title: peach, strawberry or blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Spoon evenly over margarine.
Do not stir. Combine fruit with remaining cup of sugar (may need more sugar if fruit is tart).
Bring to a boil.
Ladle over butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: hershey's triple chocolate cookies
directions: Beat oleo, sugars and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to oleo mixture, blending well.
Stir in chips.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 minute. Remove to wire rack.
Carefully press one chocolate kiss in center of each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well and spread in a dish.
Layer the lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Pour 1 jar of picante sauce over top.
Chill at least 6 hours.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef in small amount of butter.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream, cream cheese and chives.
In a 1 1/2-quart dish, alternate layers of cooked noodles, beef sauce and cream cheese mixture, ending with cream cheese layer.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy nachos
directions: Combine processed cheese spread and sour cream in saucepan; stir over low heat until processed cheese spread is melted.
On serving platter, layer half of chips, processed cheese spread mixture, tomatoes, avocados and onions; repeat layers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Season breasts with Cavender's seasoning.
Cover with dressing and let sit overnight.
Turn breasts several times.
Grill or bake in a 350° oven.

title: jugs venison roast
directions: Cut away all fat and membrane.
Place roast in slow cooker with 2 cups water; add remaining ingredients.
Cook until meat falls apart.
Makes great sandwiches served with marinated coleslaw on sesame buns.
If desired as a main dish, shorten cooking time and add one envelope brown gravy mix.
Slice and serve gravy over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: melinda's green beans and cabbage
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon. Add vinegar, sugar, onion, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Cover. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in drained beans.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Pour into serving dish and top with crisp bacon pieces.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with one cup flour.
Add fruit and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: nut meat balls(233 calories per serving)
directions: Combine all ingredients,
mixing well.
Roll into balls. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake
on
oiled cookie sheet 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with gravy or tomato sauce.
Serves 4.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except for flour in a large mixing bowl. Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing each cup well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture or with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Roll into balls, then freeze.

title: gourmet green beans
directions: Cook beans according to package directions; drain.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter; add flour, salt, pepper and Accent.
Heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat; gradually add sour cream and mustard. Heat, stirring constantly, but do not boil.
Add beans, cheese and onion to sauce.
Put in casserole.
Saute bread crumbs in 2 tablespoons butter.
Top mixture with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: layered seafood quiche
directions: Cook onion in medium saucepan, covered, over very low heat until soft, adding water if necessary to prevent scorching.
Line bottom of 9-inch pie pan with tuna.
Sprinkle with cooked onion. Top with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and salt in small bowl; mix well. Pour over cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before cutting.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old settler beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Top beans with bacon when finished baking.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water.
Squeeze and mix with other ingredients. Shape in small balls.
Brown quickly in hot butter.
Remove as they brown.
Scrape all brown particles in skillet, make a flour base gravy and put meatballs back in this.
Heat before serving.
Pour 3 tablespoons cream over balls just before serving.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Toss potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onions together.
Turn into a buttered 2-quart baking dish and season with salt and pepper.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly (do not overbake).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix broccoli, green onions, pecans and raisins.

title: 7  up  salad
directions: Warm applesauce over low heat.
Stir until cream cheese is dissolved in hot applesauce.
Add jello and dissolve. Add 7-up and mold.

title: zeppole
directions: Mix Ricotta, eggs and powdered sugar in large mixing bowl. Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Drop in hot Crisco by tablespoons.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serves about 3 dozen.

title: horseradish preserve vegetable dip(also known as 'jezebel')
directions: Blend all ingredients well with a wire whisk.
Very sharp. For milder, use 1/2 amounts of mustard and horseradish, or add additional 1/2 jar jelly and preserves.
Good with celery, green pepper, white turnips (sliced very thin) and cauliflower.
Or it can be served over cream cheese with crackers.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well.
Add undrained pineapple and bread cubes.
Bake in a shallow casserole dish at 350° for about 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until light.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop from tablespoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets with swiss cheese
directions: Arrange cutlets in a lightly greased baking dish.
Put 1 slice of cheese on each cutlet.
Mix together soup and wine until blended.
Spread evenly over meat.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top. Drizzle margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be made ahead of time.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fried corn or onion rings
directions: Mix beer, baking powder, seasoned salt, egg and flour.
Dip corn in batter; fry in deep fat at 375° until golden brown.
Place in brown paper bag with paper towels.
Will keep warm for hours.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and cool.
Use for fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Stew chicken with the 1 celery stalk and salt and pepper until done (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Remove chicken.
Strain stock and put into refrigerator until fat is firm on top.
Remove and scrape off fat.
Return stock to pan.
Add 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil and add bouillon cubes, celery, carrots and onion.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Bring back to a full boil and add noodles.
Cook until done (8 to 10 minutes).
Return deboned chicken to pot. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: easy "dump" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, dump the pineapple.
Distribute the cherry pie filling over that evenly. Over that, sprinkle the yellow cake mix evenly.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: rising to the occasion
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
In another bowl, blend 3 eggs, corn syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1/2 cup sugar until smooth. Pour mixture into the unbaked pastry crust.
Sprinkle with the chopped pecans.
Gently pour first mixture over nuts.
Bake on center oven rack for 50 to 60 minutes, until center is just set and pastry is golden.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix everything except the Jiffy mix.
Then add the Jiffy mix. Pour into a well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: snicky snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Mix pretzels, Cheerios, Rice Chex and peanuts in a large roasting pan.
Set aside.
Melt butter over a low flame.
Add Worcestershire, celery salt, garlic powder and onion salt.
Mix until blended.
Pour butter mixture over dry mixture and stir well.
Bake at 225° in a covered roaster for 1 hour.
Stir mixture.
Uncover and bake for another hour at 225°. Stir mixture.
Increase temperature to 300°.
Bake for 1/2 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: aunt val's pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Mix and put in greased Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, green peppers, onions and salt.
Place in covered container and refrigerate overnight.
Make brine by boiling sugar, vinegar and celery salt.
Cool completely.
Pour over cucumbers.
Do not remove any of the juice that comes from cucumbers.

title: pepper steak
directions: Batter steak before frying.
Oil frying pan and cook steak until brown.
Drain tomatoes, mash up and mix with remaining ingredients.
Add to steak.

title: fried rice with meat
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Saute carrots and celery.
Add meat and rice.
Stir well until each grain of rice separates and is heated through.
Add scrambled eggs and soy sauce.
Turn off heat and add green onions and salt and pepper to taste.
(You can also use any kind of vegetables.)
Serves 6.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll in balls size of buckeye. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Serve hot.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and place in a circular pattern overlapping 1/8-inch on pizza pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 325° or until light brown.
Let cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg.
Mix bananas with soda and milk; add to butter mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°, then for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit spritzer
directions: Mix frozen juice concentrate according to directions on the can, substituting soda for water.

title: south of the border enchiladas
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and saut onions for approximately 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in chicken, chiles and cream cheese. Spoon chicken mixture on center of tortilla. Roll up and place seam side down in glass baking dish (13 x 9-inch). Sprinkle with cheese and drizzle cream on top. Bake until cream thickens and cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes at 375°.

title: simple peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend egg and sugar.
Add peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with a chocolate star.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: southwestern lamb chops
directions: In sauce pan, combine Orange Juice, Jalapeno Peppers, Cumin, Salt, and Pepper. Cook over medium-high heat until mixture begins to simmer. Stir in Onion. Combine Corn Starch and Water until smooth; add to the sauce. Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook and stir for 1 minute or until thickened and bubbly. Remove from the heat. Stir in Oranges and Cilantro; keep warm.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with jello.
Add oranges and Cool Whip. Mix well.
Let set 1 hour.
Keep refrigerated.

title: bubu's peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar, Karo syrup, water, vanilla and raw peanuts.
Cook over low heat until peanuts begin to pop.
Remove from stove.
Stir in soda.
Stir well.
Spread very thin on greased pan. Set until cool.
Break into desired pieces.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, water and pumpkin.
Then add flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Mix well.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Put sugar, chocolate, milk and Karo in a large boiler and bring to a rolling boil (one that you can't stir down). Cook for 2 minutes after it begins to boil. Do not stir after sugar dissolves. Remove from stove after it cooks 2 minutes. Add the butter and let cool for 5 minutes. Add vanilla; beat until it loses gloss. Add nuts and pour quickly into buttered pan or plate. Cut when firm.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Beat well.
Add 1 egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add second egg and beat additional 5 minutes.
Make sure and beat a total of 10 minutes. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crescent danish
directions: Press 1 package rolls into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over dough in pan.
Cover with second package crescent rolls and seal.
Beat egg white until foamy and spread over top of dough. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Roll lemon until soft.
Squeeze juice in water, then slice the lemons.
Next, mix lemons and sugar in the water.
Serve ice cold.

title: chili
directions: Cook beans until tender. Brown meat and onions.
Add to beans. Add tomatoes and catsup and other ingredients.
Makes a large Dutch oven full.

title: pepperoni pizza bites
directions: Combine mozzarella cheese, pepperoni and pizza sauce in bowl. Set aside.
Flatten biscuits to 3-inch circles.
Place about 1 rounded tablespoon filling in the center of each biscuit.
Bring edges together and pinch closed with fork.
Brush with milk. Sprinkle Parmesan over biscuits.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 20.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: After chicken has been cooked, boned and cut into small pieces, put into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix the chicken broth and the cream of chicken soup together and let come to a boil.
Pour over the cut up chicken.
In another bowl, melt the margarine; add self-rising flour and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly and spoon over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Dip fry wings (may be boiled) 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small pan. Bring to a boil.
Dip cooked wings in sauce.
The more oregano added the hotter the wings!

title: easy salad
directions: Mash cottage cheese up. Add Cool Whip. Add dry jello. Add pineapple. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: wet-choc-cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Combine sugar and flour.
Bring margarine, cocoa, Wesson oil and water to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over first mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: tangy cheese ball
directions: In small deep bowl, thoroughly mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add onions, pimentos and hot sauce to mixture and blend well.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Bring to boil for 10 minutes the sugar, milk and butter.
Add the chocolate chips, vanilla, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir until chips and marshmallows are dissolved.
Chill in pan.

title: pepperoni stuffed mushrooms(microwaved)
directions: Microwave butter, onion, green peppers and chopped stems from mushrooms until tender, about 3 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.

title: english muffin bread(microwave)
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat the liquids on High for 1 1/2 minutes with one quarter turn every 30 seconds.
Add to dry mixture and stir thoroughly.
Add the rest of the flour and stir.
Spoon into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread pan (greased and sprinkled with cornmeal).
Cover with Saran Wrap and rise for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna pie
directions: Brown and drain meat; add tomato paste, spices and Mozzarella cheese and stir.
Grease 10-inch pie plate; spread cottage cheese on bottom, then add meat mixture.
Mix milk, eggs and Bisquick and pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp and eggplant dressing
directions: Cut shrimp into small pieces.
Peel eggplant.
Cut into small pieces.
Simmer eggplant over low heat in water.
Reserve liquid. Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter; add shrimp.
Saute until shrimp become pink.
Add garlic, green onions, parsley and mushrooms.
Add eggplant to shrimp mixture.
Soak bread in cooled liquid from eggplant until all is absorbed.
Combine shrimp and bread mixtures, using egg for adherence.
Season to taste with salt and peppers and mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: "green" salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Pour Ranch-style dressing over top. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Serve next day.

title: cherry refrigerator dessert
directions: Empty cherries and their syrup into a saucepan and heat to boiling.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add, all at once, to boiling cherries and cook, stirring briskly (about 5 minutes) until smoothly thickened and clear.
Remove from heat; add butter. Arrange 9 of the crackers (whole) over bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half the cherry mixture over them and sprinkle with half the nuts.
Put on another layer of whole crackers and spread remaining cherries over them.
Crumble remaining 6 crackers over top and sprinkle with rest of nuts.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: hot seafood puffs
directions: Fold mayonnaise into beaten egg whites.
Add seafood, lemon juice and dill.
Spread on toast points or toasted canape breads. Sprinkle with paprika and broil 3 minutes or until puffy and lightly brown.
This may also be used to stuff large mushrooms and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Season with oregano, chili powder, salt, pepper and catsup.
Place lettuce, tomatoes and cheese in salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and taco sauce together. When ground beef has cooled to room temperature, combine all ingredients with taco chips and toss lightly.

title: coconut balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine coconut, condensed milk, sugar, vanilla and butter.
Place in refrigerator until it becomes stiff. Form into balls.
Melt chocolate in a heavy saucepan.
Dip balls into melted chocolate.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake 1 white or yellow cake mix according to package directions.
Remove from oven.
While hot, punch holes over cake with spatula handle.
Mix together the Eagle Brand and
cream of coconut syrup; pour mixture over warm cake.
Cool, then top with the Cool Whip, mixed with the coconut.

title: crispy bars
directions: Cook first three ingredients until melted.
Can be microwaved or cooktop.
Add nuts and cereal.
Stir very well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine pudding mix, milk and orange juice.
Beat with a mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Mix in sour cream.
In a large salad bowl, combine fruits.
Gently mix in orange dressing.
Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: yellow slush punch
directions: Boil 1 cup of the measured water to dissolved jello.
Add all the remaining ingredients except 7-Up and dissolve well.
Freeze in 3 (1/2 gallon) milk or juice boxes.
Thaw to a slush and add 7-Up just before serving.
(Takes about 5 hours to thaw.)
To make red punch, substitute strawberry Kool-Aid and jello.
To make green punch, substitute lime jello and Kool-Aid.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: chocolate gobs
directions: Mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, shortening and eggs; mix well.
To the shortening mixture, add milk, vanilla and boiling water, mixing thoroughly. Gradually add the flour mixture and beat well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 5-7 minutes.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half. Stir until thickened.
Add Parmesan; cook and stir until smooth. Fold in crab.
Heat 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Toss fettucini with sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and save.
Place mushroom heads on greased cookie sheet. Chop stems and add other ingredients.
Shape into balls and place in caps. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hoppin' johns
directions: Heat peas and water to boiling in medium saucepan. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 1 hour. Fry bacon; drain. Add onion to peas; cover and simmer until peas are tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours). Stir in rice, black pepper, tomatoes and green pepper. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender, about 25 minutes. Add additional water if necessary. Add dollop of plain yogurt to each serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: slow cooker enchiladas
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper. Drain, add the following 8 ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Combine cheeses. Alternate ground beef mixture, cheese, and tortilla, starting with 3/4 c. of beef in bottom of slow cooker. Cook 5 to 7 hours on low.

title: marianne's no peek chicken
directions: Place aluminum foil in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spray foil to prevent rice from sticking.
Place rice in pan.
Add chicken. Combine soups and pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle on onion soup.
Seal foil securely.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: red, white and bleu slaw salad
directions: Combine cabbage, bacon, Bleu cheese and dressing.
Toss to combine.
Chill to let flavors blend.
When ready to serve, garnish with cherry tomatoes, cut in half and Bleu cheese.

title: hot dip(microwave)
directions: In large bowl, cook sausage in microwave until done.
Drain well.
Mix soup and tomatoes with sausage.
Cut cheese into blocks and mix with other ingredients.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 more minutes, mixing well.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: festive punch
directions: Mix juice and water.
Cut sherbet and ice cream into small pieces and put into punch bowl.
Pour juices over sherbet and ice cream and stir.

title: lemon poppy muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cream cheese at medium speed with mixer until light and fluffy. Blend in egg yolks and lemon juice.
Add combined flour, baking powder and baking soda and mix well.
Beat in poppy seed and peel. Set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add reserved 1/4 cup sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: finnish coffee bread
directions: Add yeast to lukewarm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Scald milk; add oleo until melted.
Add sugar, salt, beaten eggs and cardamom seed.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well, then add enough flour until stiff enough to handle.
Knead until smooth.
Place in bowl and brush top with melted oleo.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and form into 2 loaves or 3 pans of buns.
Place in greased pans and let rise until double in size.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes for buns and 20 minutes for bread.
The bread is delicious toasted.
Frost buns while still warm, if desired.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind all together and
add
large
handful of salt. Let stand for 1 hour, then drain this and boil 15 minutes in 1 quart vinegar.
Mix
together
flour, mustard, sugar, turmeric and 1 pint vinegar.
Add
to
first
mixture.
Cook
a little, then put in jars and seal.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugar.
Add
eggs
and beat. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately
with milk and vanilla. Bake in angel food cake pan at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tortilla pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Top tortillas with sauce, then cheese (as much as desired).
Bake on a cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes (until cheese melts).

title: grilled dill shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp, in a deep bowl.
Add shrimp and stir gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 24 hours.

title: pear salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Cut the pears (and marshmallows if necessary) into small pieces.
Combine all together.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.
May serve with maraschino cherries on top.
This will keep good for days.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in skillet.
Cook noodles for 4 minutes.
Drain, put noodles in with sauce.
Pour into baking pan and top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and turns a little brown.

title: braised fresh beef tongue
directions: Wash, then cover the tongue with boiling water and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove the skin and trim.
Place the tongue in a deep casserole with the onion, celery and carrot.

title: cherry goodie
directions: Tear cake into small pieces in an oblong baking dish. Cook pudding as directed on box. While pudding is warm, add sour cream. Blend well. Pour over cake and chill. When cold, spoon pie filling over top and chill.

title: jello-strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries and pineapple.
Pour 1 layer in small dish.
Chill slightly.
Layer sour cream.
Add rest of jello mixture; chill.
May be doubled for company.

title: swedish apple pie(quick and easy)
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate and fill with apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
In a bowl, cream oleo (butter) and sugar.
Add egg and flour; mix well.
Drop over apples and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
May be served with vanilla ice cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix soups, milk and taco mix.
Add meat.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole 1/2 tortillas, 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread apples in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Mix with a fork and sprinkle remaining ingredients over apples.
Bake about 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: souse
directions: Cook the feet with water (to cover), salt, pepper and 1 cup vinegar for approximately 30 minutes.
Then add all other ingredients and cook until all meats are cooked to the degree of doneness desired.
Serves a crowd and is eaten with a fork as the feet will mostly cook off the bones.
This is extremely good served with Hoppin' Jack (black-eyed peas, rice and bacon ends), greens, candied yams, salad and corn bread.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate for 2 days.
Stir each day.

title: cucumber mousse salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and let set (to soft-set stage).
Add the sour cream and cucumber.
Pour into mold and chill until solid.
Decorate with edible flowers and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together and pour into ungreased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: maple oatmeal cookies(makes 42 cookies)
directions: Combine the oats, flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon in a large bowl and stir to mix well.
Add the maple syrup, egg, water or juice, canola oil and vanilla extract and stir to mix well.
Stir in the nuts and fruit.

Coat a large baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and drop rounded teaspoonful of the dough onto the sheet, spacing them at least 1-inch apart. Flatten each cookie slightly with the tip of a spoon.
Bake the cookies at 300° for about 14 minutes or until the cookies have spread and appear dry around the edges.
(They will not brown significantly during baking.)
Remove the cookies from the oven and cool on the sheet for 3 minutes.
Then transfer the cookies to wire racks to cool completely.
Serve immediately or transfer to an airtight container until ready to serve.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 2 cups hot water.
Add other ingredients and mix with mixer.
Cook at 375° until done.
Dough will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: sea soup
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart pan, mix chicken broth, ginger and soy sauce; bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce to a simmer; add imitation crab and carrot and simmer, uncovered, until hot, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add green onions and sesame oil. Pour into a soup tureen to serve at the table, or ladle into 2 or 4 individual bowls.
Garnish with egg slices.
Makes 2 entree or 4 first-course servings.

title: peanut cups
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place 1 teaspoon melted chocolate in each baking cup and roll cup to have chocolate line inside.
Chill until hard. Fill cup with cheese mixture.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs; combine flour, soda and salt.
Sift.
Add to first mixture.
Add bananas.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on.
Skin and coarsely grate potatoes into large bowl.
Heat margarine with soup; add onion and blend in sour cream.
Lightly stir in cheese.
Add this mixture to the potatoes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle buttered corn flakes over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: charlie's chocolate raisin laceys
directions: Rinse and drain raisins.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful two inches apart on greased cookie sheets (do not use air-bake or Teflon sheets).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen very thin, lacy cookies.

title: carrot salad
directions: Clean carrots and slice julienne style.
Cook in 2-inches salt water until crisp-tender.
Finely dice remaining vegetables and add to cooked carrots.

title: broccoli blue cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain and set aside. In a saucepan, blend margarine, flour, salt and cheese.
Add 1 cup of milk all at once and cook, stirring, until mixture boils.
Stir in the broccoli.
Pour into greased 1-quart size ovenproof dish. Top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: governor's mansion rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast in a large jar and let stand 30 minutes. (Be sure it's large enough or it will come over top.) Sift flour into mixing bowl. Add salt, shortening, egg and water mixture. Mix well. Let stand for 2 hours. Roll out, cut out, place on baking sheet and let stand another 2 hours or until rolls rise. Bake at 375° until brown. (You may have to add more flour.)

title: noodle kugel
directions: Beat eggs and brown sugar.
Mix all ingredients together and put into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice until it gets thick; add pecans, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Spread on top pecans and put cherries around it.
Refrigerate.

title: causa limena (lima potato salad)
directions: Boil the potatoes and mash them with the oil, lemon juice, salt and crushed garlic.
Mix thoroughly.
Place half the mixture in a bowl and add tuna fish, mayonnaise and celery.
Cover with the rest of the potato mixture.
Decorate with hard-boiled eggs and lettuce.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain 1 jar artichokes.
Saute onion in liquid from artichokes. Beat eggs and add artichokes (both jars) which have been slightly chopped, along with the juice from second jar.
To this mixture, add remaining ingredients and sauteed onion.
Spray a 7 x 11-inch dish with Pam and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Freezes well.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth. Add biscuit mix; mix well. Chill for
1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool.

title: boursin chicken with walnuts
directions: Combine Boursin, carrots, walnuts and flour.
Place about 2 ounces of the mixture into the center of
each chicken breast and roll up.

title: custard
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat until creamy.
Pour in buttermilk, vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: freezer grilled sandwich for future company
directions: I put everything through my meat grinder.
Spread on bun halves and freeze until ready to use.
Heat in broiler until evenly browned.

title: pineapple spareribs
directions: Bring ingredients to boil.
Add spareribs.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple syrup.
Thicken with cornstarch. Add pineapple chunks.

title: fruit scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients with butter until crumbly.
Add currants, apricots, sugar and cream.
Knead gently.
Cut dough in half.
Pat each half into a circle and cut into 8 wedges.
Brush top with reserved cream and sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes and then test for doneness.
Makes 16 scones.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until firm.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Brown meat; add onion, oregano, garlic salt and chili powder. Add tomatoes last.
Simmer these ingredients for 20 to 30 minutes. Add 1/2 cup water to keep from drying (more if needed).
Add cheese chunks, stirring until melted.
Serve warm with nacho chips.
Better if chips aren't salted.

title: quick sweet rolls
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit fourths in mixture of white sugar and cinnamon.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla ice cream and margarine. Boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let set in pan for 2 minutes.
Tip onto aluminum foil covered cookie sheet.
Eat and enjoy.

title: venison stew in crock-pot
directions: Salt and pepper venison cubes.
Brown lightly in 2 tablespoons butter or oil.
Put celery and onion in crock-pot.
Add browned meat cubes and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 12 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans. Bake 60 minutes at 350° or until bread is done.

title: okra goulash
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add okra and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add corn and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: janet's banana bread
directions: Mix margarine and sugar, then add bananas and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour sifted with soda, and last nuts (optional).
Bake in loaf pan at 350 for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Add flour and almond extract; spread evenly into greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Using a knife, mark off 24 squares in the surface of the batter.

Put 3 or 4 cherries from can of pie filling into the center of each square. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until surface is lightly browned. Remove from oven; immediately dust generously with confectioners sugar.
Cool completely and cut.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix and shake well.
Crumbled Blue cheese to taste may be added.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put in a medium size pan the cocoa, sugar, milk and oleo. Cook the mixture for 2 minutes after it begins to boil, then take the pan off the stove.
Add the oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Beat the mixture until it is cool enough and stiff enough to drop on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: stuffed meat loaf squares and parmesan potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have two 8-inch square baking dishes ready.
Mix beef, bread crumbs, 1/3 of the ketchup, the milk and egg in a large bowl until blended.
Pat 1/2 of the mixture into the bottom of one baking dish.
Sprinkle with layer of spinach, then cheese.
Pat remaining meat mixture on top, then add the rest of the ketchup.
Meanwhile, put butter in the other baking dish and place in oven, 1 to 2 minutes until melted.
Remove from oven. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Dip cut side of potatoes into butter, then press into Parmesan.
Place cheese side up in baking dish.
Bake meat loaf and potatoes, side by side, 30 to 35 minutes until meat is no longer pink near center and potatoes are tender and golden brown on top.
Cut meat loaf into four squares.

title: death by chocolate
directions: *Instead of the alcohol you may substitute a mixture of 1 teaspoon sugar and 4 tablespoons leftover black coffee.

title: fantasy flower cookie
directions: What to do:
Mix 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, 1 cup margarine or butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll each half 3/16-inch thick on a lightly floured cloth-covered board. Cut into circles.
Place on lightly greased sheet and bake until edges are light brown, 7 or 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk on high heat until boiling, then turn to medium heat and continue to boil for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour in pan and let set.

title: orange yogurt loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir dry ingredients together.
In small bowl, combine melted butter, eggs, orange rind and orange juice; blend thoroughly.
Beat in dry ingredients alternately with yogurt until blended.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix soda with water and add to flour mixture. Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Combine oats and brown sugar.
Blend in butter and syrup. Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° (??? minutes in a microwave).
Cool

title: ben's buckeyes
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate.
Roll into little balls and freeze.
Melt chocolate bark and dip balls into the chocolate with a toothpick.
Lay on wax paper and let harden.
